WEBVTT

00:03.133 --> 00:05.005
[grand orchestral fanfare
playing]

00:31.248 --> 00:33.337
[insects chirping]

00:37.994 --> 00:40.040
[soft growling]

00:46.829 --> 00:48.874
[animal cries in distance]

00:58.014 --> 01:00.060
[soft growling nearby]

01:11.462 --> 01:13.551
[lions groaning]

01:15.771 --> 01:17.816
[groaning stops]

01:23.953 --> 01:25.694
[lion cries in pain nearby]

01:43.799 --> 01:45.888
♪

01:52.024 --> 01:53.809
[rustling nearby]

02:00.207 --> 02:02.339
[lion growls softly nearby]

02:02.383 --> 02:04.646
CHIPO [whispers]:
Abduya. Abduya!

02:07.605 --> 02:09.694
♪

02:17.876 --> 02:19.922
[rustling nearby]

02:28.452 --> 02:30.541
♪

02:42.553 --> 02:44.512
[rustling nearby]

02:44.555 --> 02:46.209
Chipo.

02:48.472 --> 02:50.561
-Chipo.
-[rustling continues]

02:53.477 --> 02:55.175
Chipo.

02:58.047 --> 03:00.136
[grunting]

03:01.703 --> 03:03.748
[men speaking TshiVenda]

03:17.893 --> 03:19.982
[engine starts]

03:24.639 --> 03:26.728
♪

03:32.690 --> 03:34.039
-[snapping sound]
-[gasps]

03:34.083 --> 03:35.606
[Abduya yells in distance]

03:35.650 --> 03:37.173
-Abduya?
-[soft growling]

03:37.217 --> 03:39.393
[Abduya screaming]

03:39.436 --> 03:41.656
[quiet snarling]

03:41.699 --> 03:43.571
Abduya?

03:45.050 --> 03:47.139
[panting]

03:52.710 --> 03:55.800
-[Abduya groaning]
-[gasps] Abduya.

03:55.844 --> 03:57.933
[Mizozi speaking TshiVenda]

04:03.155 --> 04:05.375
-[rope whooshes]
-[pained yelp]

04:05.419 --> 04:07.551
[rope creaking]

04:07.595 --> 04:09.684
[grunting]

04:13.209 --> 04:15.646
[roars]

04:21.435 --> 04:23.524
♪

04:31.009 --> 04:33.098
NATE:
Where are you, my love?

04:34.796 --> 04:36.711
I can't find you.

04:39.191 --> 04:40.889
-I need you.
-[airplane engine buzzing]

04:40.932 --> 04:42.717
PILOT:
Requesting permission to land.

04:42.760 --> 04:44.458
-[radio static blares]
-MAN [on radio]: Zulu, Sierra,

04:44.501 --> 04:46.590
Papa, Mike, Victor,
cleared to land.

04:48.375 --> 04:51.508
-Did you say something to me?
-Mm-mm.

04:51.552 --> 04:53.684
Is this your first time
in South Africa?

04:53.728 --> 04:57.209
No. No,
but it was another lifetime.

04:58.428 --> 05:00.212
Wow. So beautiful.

05:00.256 --> 05:03.172
["N'na Duniyaa"
by Sona Jobarteh playing]

05:04.129 --> 05:06.349
Hey, Norah.

05:06.393 --> 05:08.133
Mare?

05:08.177 --> 05:10.571
Hey, look out the window.

05:17.969 --> 05:19.362
[Norah gasps]

05:19.406 --> 05:21.059
NORAH:
Mare.

05:21.103 --> 05:22.713
-Mare. Look at them.
-Yeah.

05:22.757 --> 05:26.326
♪ Nying duniyaa kono

05:26.369 --> 05:29.851
♪ Koleyaal ka ké lé

05:29.894 --> 05:33.463
♪ Duniyaa

05:33.507 --> 05:36.553
♪ Si n'nyoo'séeyaa...

05:36.597 --> 05:38.773
-Go that way.
-I'm so hot. My God, Dad.

05:38.816 --> 05:40.688
-My eyes are sweating.
-NATE: Thank you so much.

05:40.731 --> 05:42.733
-PILOT: You're welcome.
-Everything is sweating.

05:42.777 --> 05:44.692
-My spleen is sweating.
-Your spleen?

05:44.735 --> 05:46.607
The sweat on my spleen
is sweating.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.435
-[Nate grunting]
-Oh, my gosh.

05:48.478 --> 05:49.871
Heinously hot.

05:49.914 --> 05:52.090
I'm melting, Mare.

05:52.134 --> 05:53.744
Stuff's got to breathe.

05:53.788 --> 05:55.485
[panting]

05:55.529 --> 05:57.226
NORAH:
JFK to London,

05:57.269 --> 06:00.055
London to Johannesburg,
Johannesburg to Polokwane,

06:00.098 --> 06:02.579
and Polokwane to the middle
of freaking nowhere.

06:02.623 --> 06:04.233
Where are we right now?

06:04.276 --> 06:06.453
NATE:
The bush.

06:06.496 --> 06:08.324
NORAH:
Do they have one of those fans

06:08.368 --> 06:09.760
that, you know, like,
squirt water?

06:09.804 --> 06:11.109
-NATE: Hello, Tata.
-Hello.

06:11.153 --> 06:12.546
NATE:
Hey. Hey.

06:12.589 --> 06:14.330
[Nate and Norah sighing]

06:14.374 --> 06:15.723
NATE:
Norah, you want some water?

06:15.766 --> 06:18.334
-Take some water.
-[Norah groans]

06:18.378 --> 06:20.423
NORAH:
Dad, are you sure he's coming?

06:20.467 --> 06:23.470
Well, I hope so,

06:23.513 --> 06:26.951
'cause an Uber would take
a long time to get here.

06:26.995 --> 06:28.431
Whew!

06:28.475 --> 06:30.477
[Nate and Norah panting]

06:30.520 --> 06:32.870
-It's so hot. I need water.
-How about it, Mare?

06:32.914 --> 06:34.959
Come on. Africa?

06:37.222 --> 06:39.921
-Oh, my God. It's so hot.
-Come on, baby. Talk to me.

06:42.271 --> 06:44.273
Oh, I think that's him.
It is him.

06:44.316 --> 06:45.579
[chuckling]:
Hey.

06:45.622 --> 06:47.189
Air conditioner.

06:47.232 --> 06:49.321
-NATE: Hey, he made it.
-[Martin laughs]

06:49.365 --> 06:51.454
-I have no words.
-Wow. Look at this.

06:51.498 --> 06:53.195
-NATE: Look at you, guy.
-[chuckling]

06:53.238 --> 06:54.936
-How are you, bro?
-What's up, man?

06:54.979 --> 06:57.939
[grunting, laughing]

06:57.982 --> 07:00.289
-Ah, man.
-How-how was the flight?

07:00.332 --> 07:02.030
-Good. It was real good.
-Yeah?

07:02.073 --> 07:03.466
-Remember Norah?
-Oh, my goodness.

07:03.510 --> 07:05.076
Martin. Oh, my gosh.

07:05.120 --> 07:06.687
BOTH: The last time I saw you,
you were just a...

07:06.730 --> 07:08.471
-NORAH: ...little half a man.
-Okay.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.212
-You are getting
so much taller. -Okay.

07:10.255 --> 07:12.170
-Wow. You're getting so much
more witty. -All grown-up.

07:12.214 --> 07:13.998
And, Meredith,
how's the teenage life?

07:14.042 --> 07:15.565
It's just "Mare."

07:15.609 --> 07:17.480
-Mare. Okay.
-Here you go, brother.

07:17.524 --> 07:19.351
Here we go. Wow. Okay.

07:19.395 --> 07:22.180
Yeah, let's give you guys
a hand here.

07:22.224 --> 07:24.139
-Let's go.
-NATE: All right.

07:24.182 --> 07:25.880
Welcome to Mopane, guys.

07:25.923 --> 07:27.838
NORAH:  Are you, like,
one of those game wardens?

07:27.882 --> 07:29.536
MARTIN:
I've had to sort of become, uh,

07:29.579 --> 07:31.625
like an enforcer
for the reserve.

07:31.668 --> 07:33.496
NORAH:
Enforcer?

07:33.540 --> 07:35.672
MARTIN:
Yeah. Safari's big business.

07:35.716 --> 07:37.500
A lot of pressure on all sides.

07:37.544 --> 07:39.154
One way or another,
everyone depends

07:39.197 --> 07:41.765
on the animals
for their survival.

07:41.809 --> 07:44.681
Oh, this is Mom's village.

07:44.725 --> 07:47.467
Yeah. I first met your mom
when I was a kid.

07:47.510 --> 07:49.817
Used to come up here
on family holidays.

07:49.860 --> 07:51.514
Met her and her friends.

07:51.558 --> 07:53.473
They taught me
all about the area.

07:53.516 --> 07:56.606
Actually, uh,
got me interested in wildlife.

07:56.650 --> 08:00.218
And after university,
I introduced her to your dad.

08:01.568 --> 08:04.484
["N'na Duniyaa" continues,
singer vocalizing]

08:04.527 --> 08:07.574
♪ Indalo ilimeele

08:09.837 --> 08:12.317
[singer vocalizing]

08:12.361 --> 08:14.885
♪ Indalo ilimeele

08:14.929 --> 08:17.148
♪ Ilimeele...

08:17.192 --> 08:18.759
NATE:
Whew!

08:18.802 --> 08:21.109
I got some memories here, boy.

08:21.152 --> 08:23.198
-MARTIN: There you go.
-NATE [chuckling]: Whew!

08:24.895 --> 08:26.244
Whew!

08:26.288 --> 08:28.551
-Looks all good, man.
-Yep, yep. Yeah.

08:28.595 --> 08:30.640
It's the nicest it's looked
in a long time, 'cause I knew

08:30.684 --> 08:31.815
-I had guests coming.
-Oh, sorry.

08:31.859 --> 08:33.077
-MARE: It's okay.
-You did?

08:33.121 --> 08:34.426
MARTIN:
Yeah. [chuckles]

08:34.470 --> 08:36.472
-Okay.
-Come on. This way.

08:36.516 --> 08:37.952
[Martin grunts]

08:37.995 --> 08:40.302
[birds calling]

08:40.345 --> 08:44.001
NATE: Wow, man. You really
looked after the place.

08:44.045 --> 08:45.655
Is that the, uh, Bantam?

08:45.699 --> 08:47.439
-MARTIN: Yep. Yep.
-No.

08:47.483 --> 08:48.745
You still didn't fix it?

08:48.789 --> 08:50.530
No, I was waiting
for you to come back

08:50.573 --> 08:52.183
-and see if you could get it
running. -Me? Yeah, right.

08:52.227 --> 08:54.272
-It goes straight up.
-MARE: Okay.

08:54.316 --> 08:56.666
Just through that one
on the left, guys.

08:56.710 --> 08:58.538
-Wow.
-Yeah.

08:58.581 --> 09:01.149
Hey, man, uh, thank you so much
for having us.

09:01.192 --> 09:03.804
-Yeah, of course, man.
-We really needed it.

09:03.847 --> 09:05.762
-Anytime, bro. Anytime.
-NORAH: Is it this door?

09:05.806 --> 09:07.503
Right through that door. Yeah.

09:07.547 --> 09:08.852
-MARE: You need help?
-MARTIN: Just kick it.

09:08.896 --> 09:10.288
Sometimes it sticks. Yeah.

09:10.332 --> 09:12.203
MARE: Put strength
into your foot, Norah.

09:12.247 --> 09:13.683
-Come on, bigfoot. You got it.
-MARTIN: Okay, wow. That's...

09:13.727 --> 09:14.945
[Norah laughing]

09:14.989 --> 09:16.991
MARTIN:
There we go.

09:17.034 --> 09:18.732
Get some light.

09:18.775 --> 09:21.256
Oh, guys, don't worry
about your shoes, please.

09:21.299 --> 09:22.953
Since my last girlfriend left,

09:22.997 --> 09:24.825
I've been living
like a bachelor.

09:24.868 --> 09:27.088
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah, place is a real mess.

09:27.131 --> 09:28.785
You'll have to excuse it.

09:28.829 --> 09:30.570
-NORAH: So, um, Uncle Martin.
-Yeah?

09:30.613 --> 09:32.397
What's your Wi-Fi password?

09:32.441 --> 09:34.182
Just so I can, you know, like,
connect to it or something.

09:34.225 --> 09:35.836
Oh, yeah, sorry.
We don't actually have Wi-Fi

09:35.879 --> 09:37.925
or cell phone signal here
for the next ten days.

09:37.968 --> 09:39.448
-What?
-What are you gonna do?

09:39.491 --> 09:41.015
-No. No, no.
-MARTIN: Yeah.

09:41.058 --> 09:42.538
-That's not fair.
-NATE: No, you'll be all right.

09:42.582 --> 09:43.974
-MARE: Whatever.
-NORAH: What? [sighs]

09:44.018 --> 09:45.367
MARTIN:
There's plenty to see, though.

09:45.410 --> 09:47.369
Don't worry.
You won't miss your phone.

09:47.412 --> 09:49.110
NORAH:
This is so back-in-the-day.

09:49.153 --> 09:50.546
MARTIN [chuckling]:
Yeah.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.983
So, ladies,
you are through here.

09:53.027 --> 09:54.985
Uh, sorry. I know
it doesn't look like much,

09:55.029 --> 09:57.901
but they're more comfortable
than they look.

10:00.469 --> 10:02.036
Did Mom shoot some of these?

10:02.079 --> 10:03.777
Oh, wow. You still got these?

10:03.820 --> 10:06.083
-Yeah, of course, man.
-Okay.

10:06.127 --> 10:08.651
Oh. This...

10:08.695 --> 10:11.654
This little bump right here,
you know who that is?

10:11.698 --> 10:13.830
That's you.

10:13.874 --> 10:15.919
♪

10:17.747 --> 10:19.793
MARE:
These photos are amazing.

10:19.836 --> 10:21.664
NORAH:
Wow.

10:21.708 --> 10:23.666
MARE: Mom looks so young
and beautiful.

10:23.710 --> 10:25.450
Where'd she shoot this one?

10:25.494 --> 10:26.930
MARTIN:
That's just up the road here.

10:26.974 --> 10:28.540
MARE:
I love this tree.

10:28.584 --> 10:30.325
-Is that a self-portrait?
-MARTIN: Yeah.

10:30.368 --> 10:31.718
She spent so much time there,

10:31.761 --> 10:33.589
we actually called it
the Amahle Tree.

10:33.633 --> 10:36.461
She loved to photograph
that thing.

10:36.505 --> 10:38.507
-Can you take that salad
through for us? -Okay.

10:38.550 --> 10:40.683
NATE:
Mmm. Mmm, mmm, mmm.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.598
Smells good. Mmm.

10:42.642 --> 10:44.731
-Yep. It's ready, man.
-Okay.

10:44.774 --> 10:47.168
[Nate chuckles]

10:47.211 --> 10:49.692
All right. Where's Mare?

10:49.736 --> 10:51.694
Uh, she's in there unpacking.

10:51.738 --> 10:53.391
Oh. Okay.

10:55.002 --> 10:57.265
-Hey, Mare.
-Hey.

10:57.308 --> 10:58.919
Dinner's ready.

10:58.962 --> 11:00.703
Thanks.

11:02.270 --> 11:05.142
So, you got
everything you need?

11:05.186 --> 11:07.144
I was the one who packed
your suitcase, Dad.

11:07.188 --> 11:08.711
Yes, yes, you did.
Yes, you did.

11:08.755 --> 11:11.845
So, did I get
everything I need?

11:15.544 --> 11:17.154
Hey, dinner's ready, okay?

11:17.198 --> 11:18.721
You just said that.

11:18.765 --> 11:21.158
No, I know I just said that.
I just, uh...

11:27.164 --> 11:28.949
And this is all with the...
the long exposure

11:28.992 --> 11:30.602
-with your mom's...
your mom's old Nikon? -Mm-hmm.

11:30.646 --> 11:31.952
Oh, yeah. We got to restock.

11:31.995 --> 11:33.083
MARE: Some people think
it's old-school,

11:33.127 --> 11:34.432
but I just prefer film.

11:34.476 --> 11:35.738
Film is old-school,
but, I mean...

11:35.782 --> 11:37.044
-I love shooting with film.
-Yeah?

11:37.087 --> 11:38.959
-Yeah.
-That is really amazing.

11:39.002 --> 11:40.656
-Thank you.
-Eh? Nate, you see this?

11:40.700 --> 11:42.658
-Look at this work.
-NATE: Oh, yeah.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.486
-Eh? -No, I haven't seen
that one, but, uh...

11:44.529 --> 11:46.227
-It's just like your mom's
stuff. -[sighs]: Yeah.

11:46.270 --> 11:47.750
-It's actually got the same
kind of soul to it. -Yeah.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.752
-You are really talented.
-MARE: I applied to

11:49.796 --> 11:51.711
the Tisch School of the Arts
at NYU.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.234
MARTIN: Okay, okay. Is that
a big... it's a big art school?

11:53.277 --> 11:55.018
-MARE: Oh, is it?
-NATE: Yeah, it's a big school.

11:55.062 --> 11:56.716
-MARE: It's the best school.
-Well, you're gonna get in.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.369
-MARE: Thank you. I hope I do.
-MARTIN: Wow. Yeah.

11:58.413 --> 11:59.893
MARTIN: She's gonna get in.
Watch. Mark my words.

11:59.936 --> 12:01.677
NATE: She didn't apply
for the medical school

12:01.721 --> 12:03.548
-like Daddy wanted.
-MARTIN: No, and she shouldn't.

12:03.592 --> 12:04.941
No, you shouldn't, 'cause one
doctor's enough in your family.

12:04.985 --> 12:06.638
-Everything...
-NATE: What? No, look.

12:06.682 --> 12:07.770
No, I-I tell her all the time
that I love her work.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.206
She got that, um...

12:09.250 --> 12:11.339
What is that, uh,
one that's on the fridge?

12:11.382 --> 12:13.036
It's like, uh, a blue car,

12:13.080 --> 12:14.646
-and there's a building
in the back. -[Norah chuckles]

12:14.690 --> 12:17.606
Dad, the car is not blue.
It's red.

12:17.649 --> 12:19.216
-NATE: It's not red.
-It's red.

12:19.260 --> 12:21.131
-NATE: It's blue, right?
-It's a red car, Dad,

12:21.175 --> 12:23.046
-and that was five years ago.
-NATE: Oh.

12:23.090 --> 12:24.874
Sorry, I meant red.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.876
-MARE: Yeah, of course you did.
-I said blue, uh, but it...

12:26.920 --> 12:30.532
Okay, uh, what are you into
nowadays, young lady?

12:30.575 --> 12:32.839
This minute, I'm thinking
about going into psychology.

12:32.882 --> 12:34.797
-Mare. -You know,
family therapy, maybe.

12:34.841 --> 12:36.625
-Hey. Mare. Mare.
-MARTIN: Probably a good idea.

12:36.668 --> 12:38.061
If you got a problem, just...

12:38.105 --> 12:39.497
-MARTIN: Come on. Nate, just...
-...just say it.

12:39.541 --> 12:41.369
My problem is that
in the last ten minutes,

12:41.412 --> 12:43.632
Martin just showed more
interest in my photography

12:43.675 --> 12:45.242
than you have in the last year.

12:45.286 --> 12:47.070
-What? -Which is
the same amount of time

12:47.114 --> 12:49.420
that you showed our mother
in the last year of her life.

12:49.464 --> 12:50.639
NORAH:
Mare.

12:50.682 --> 12:52.597
She got sick.

12:52.641 --> 12:54.121
You missed it

12:54.164 --> 12:55.687
-'cause you had already
left us. -No, no, no.

12:55.731 --> 12:57.385
-No, it's not what happened.
I tried. -Dad.

12:57.428 --> 12:59.430
Your mother and I,
we mutually...

12:59.474 --> 13:01.824
mutually agreed to separate,

13:01.868 --> 13:03.521
-and then she got sick.
-[sighs]

13:03.565 --> 13:05.697
-Norah, no, don't go.
-MARE: It's okay.

13:05.741 --> 13:07.743
-I'll go to her, Dad. -Come on.
What are you talking about?

13:07.787 --> 13:09.092
Norah. Hey, Norah?

13:09.136 --> 13:10.659
Sorry, I shouldn't have
brought this up.

13:10.702 --> 13:12.661
Not in front of Norah.

13:12.704 --> 13:14.794
[Nate sighs]

13:14.837 --> 13:16.926
-[Martin sighs]
-MARE [distant]: You okay?

13:16.970 --> 13:19.276
Got us another bottle
before we can't stand up.

13:19.320 --> 13:21.278
Ah. Always thinking ahead.

13:21.322 --> 13:23.324
-That's what I like about you.
-[sighs]: Yeah.

13:23.367 --> 13:24.542
Okay?

13:24.586 --> 13:28.285
In a pinch, I have been known,

13:28.329 --> 13:30.070
-on occasion...
-Mm-hmm.

13:30.113 --> 13:32.899
...when necessary,

13:32.942 --> 13:35.945
to crawl around my house
on all fours

13:35.989 --> 13:37.773
looking for another bottle.

13:37.817 --> 13:39.731
[Nate laughing]

13:39.775 --> 13:41.821
The house.
What a... What about the yard?

13:41.864 --> 13:44.127
-Uh, yeah.
-What about the yard?

13:44.171 --> 13:46.129
The garden.
Definitely the garden.

13:46.173 --> 13:48.131
[laughing]

13:49.567 --> 13:50.873
-Mmm.
-What do you got?

13:50.917 --> 13:52.179
-That's a bit much.
-Too strong?

13:52.222 --> 13:53.397
Yeah, a little strong.

13:53.441 --> 13:55.443
-Lord. [laughs]
-Hey.

13:55.486 --> 13:57.140
Cheers, man.

13:57.184 --> 13:58.925
It's good to have you back.

13:58.968 --> 14:00.840
[Martin groans]

14:04.408 --> 14:06.367
[Martin sighs]

14:06.410 --> 14:08.586
[Nate sniffs]

14:08.630 --> 14:10.719
Can I ask you a question?

14:17.944 --> 14:20.163
Why didn't you come
to the funeral?

14:23.906 --> 14:26.126
Okay. Um, honestly?

14:27.214 --> 14:29.303
Yeah. Why?

14:30.870 --> 14:34.438
I... didn't want
to see her buried

14:34.482 --> 14:37.441
in a concrete plot
in New York City.

14:40.270 --> 14:42.751
I didn't...
couldn't stomach it,

14:42.794 --> 14:44.492
and I didn't think that that's

14:44.535 --> 14:46.233
what she would've wanted,
either.

14:47.408 --> 14:50.541
Maybe we should just agree
to leave it at that.

14:53.240 --> 14:56.373
You know, Mare is right.

14:56.417 --> 14:58.767
Come on, man.
She's in a lot of pain.

14:58.810 --> 15:01.335
Yeah, she is. And she fights.

15:01.378 --> 15:03.685
Man, she fights
just like her mom.

15:03.728 --> 15:06.470
[chuckling]:
She does. Yeah.

15:06.514 --> 15:08.429
What I wouldn't do
to fight with that woman

15:08.472 --> 15:10.518
just one more time.

15:13.086 --> 15:15.218
Now my wife's gone.

15:15.262 --> 15:17.220
Mare's gone.

15:17.264 --> 15:20.006
Norah is hanging on
by a thread.

15:21.311 --> 15:23.139
See, I missed all the signs.

15:23.183 --> 15:25.794
I missed all the signs
of my marriage.

15:25.837 --> 15:28.362
I missed the signs of my kids.

15:31.713 --> 15:34.672
And I missed the signs
of her cancer.

15:34.716 --> 15:36.109
That's not your fault.

15:36.152 --> 15:37.501
That's not how it works.

15:37.545 --> 15:38.981
I... Hey, hey,
I'm a doctor, okay?

15:39.025 --> 15:40.983
I'm a doctor, and I know
what death looks like.

15:41.027 --> 15:44.073
And I know that death
walked up the steps

15:44.117 --> 15:46.858
to where my kids
and my wife were sleeping,

15:46.902 --> 15:48.730
knocked on the door,
and guess what.

15:48.773 --> 15:51.428
I wasn't home.

15:51.472 --> 15:54.518
I wasn't home...

15:54.562 --> 15:57.434
to look it in the eye
and say, "No.

16:00.350 --> 16:03.092
No, you can't take her."

16:04.485 --> 16:06.661
I failed those kids.

16:06.704 --> 16:08.619
Do you understand?

16:11.883 --> 16:13.537
It's why we're here.

16:13.581 --> 16:15.887
Stop beating yourself up, Nate.

16:15.931 --> 16:17.977
This cancer was always
gonna kill her.

16:18.020 --> 16:20.022
Nothing you could do.

16:24.809 --> 16:26.898
♪

16:28.248 --> 16:29.597
[grunts]

16:30.815 --> 16:32.469
[sighs]

16:32.513 --> 16:34.384
I wasn't there, man.

16:36.473 --> 16:38.171
[sighs]

16:38.214 --> 16:39.999
[softly]:
I wasn't there.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.002
[birds chirping]

16:47.832 --> 16:49.747
BANJI [over radio]:
Yes. Same place as last time.

16:49.791 --> 16:51.358
MARTIN:
Yeah, copy that.

16:51.401 --> 16:53.795
In the valley
by the abandoned schoolhouse.

16:53.838 --> 16:55.797
Thanks, Banji.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.364
-NATE: Hey.
-Morning, big guy.

16:57.407 --> 16:58.800
How's your head?

16:58.843 --> 17:00.323
Ah, little fuzzy.

17:00.367 --> 17:02.499
Yeah, mine, too.
Everything all right?

17:02.543 --> 17:05.328
Yeah. I'm gonna give you guys
the VIP tour today.

17:05.372 --> 17:06.938
We'll go through
the private section

17:06.982 --> 17:08.853
of the reserve,
avoid the tourists.

17:08.897 --> 17:10.464
-Morning. -What do you mean,
"give me the hat"? It's my hat.

17:10.507 --> 17:12.161
-Just be us and the wildlife.
-It's not your hat.

17:12.205 --> 17:13.684
-MARTIN: Morning, ladies.
-Mare, it says so very clearly

17:13.728 --> 17:15.121
right here on the tag
that this is my hat.

17:15.164 --> 17:16.644
Just because you wrote
your name on a hat

17:16.687 --> 17:18.298
-doesn't mean it's now yours.
-Mare, honestly,

17:18.341 --> 17:20.082
-this is my hat. -Just give me
my hat, please. Come on.

17:20.126 --> 17:21.605
NATE: Hey, guys. Uncle Martin
just said good morning.

17:21.649 --> 17:23.216
MARE and NORAH:
Good morning, Uncle Martin.

17:23.259 --> 17:24.956
-NORAH: Mare, it's my hat.
-MARE: It's not your hat.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.871
-I'm the one who packed it.
-Here you go, Mare. Okay?

17:26.915 --> 17:28.699
-NORAH: You don't even need it.
-That settles the hat issues.

17:28.743 --> 17:30.179
NORAH: It's too small to even
fit your big ol' head anyway.

17:30.223 --> 17:31.746
-[engine starts]
-Now you're ready for safari.

17:31.789 --> 17:33.530
MARE:
Yes. Where are we heading?

17:33.574 --> 17:36.446
MARTIN: Uh, to see some of
the most incredible creatures

17:36.490 --> 17:38.448
on the planet, hopefully.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.494
[birds calling]

17:40.537 --> 17:42.626
♪

17:52.593 --> 17:54.464
NORAH and MARE [singsongy]:
We got Milkshake Mare.

17:54.508 --> 17:57.119
We got Mini Nugget Norah.

17:57.163 --> 17:59.861
We got McDouble Martin.

17:59.904 --> 18:02.820
And Supersize Nugget Nate.

18:02.864 --> 18:05.736
♪

18:07.869 --> 18:10.132
Look at that just... Waterbuck.

18:13.353 --> 18:15.311
Here, here, here, here.
Giraffe.

18:15.355 --> 18:17.531
NORAH:
Oh, my gosh. They're so cute.

18:18.445 --> 18:21.926
♪

18:30.631 --> 18:32.154
[trumpeting]

18:35.201 --> 18:36.724
[birds screeching]

18:38.987 --> 18:41.032
There's the old schoolhouse.

18:41.076 --> 18:43.905
So Banji will be
just around the corner here.

18:45.776 --> 18:47.735
MARE:  They put a school
in the middle of rocks?

18:47.778 --> 18:49.780
MARTIN:  Yeah.
It used to be used by the...

18:49.824 --> 18:52.870
families that worked in
the mine over the hill there.

18:52.914 --> 18:55.917
But then the copper mine
ran dry,

18:55.960 --> 18:58.441
so, uh, they shut down
the school.

18:59.399 --> 19:01.488
Ah, there's our man.

19:10.279 --> 19:13.282
Stay close to the vehicle,
please, okay?

19:13.326 --> 19:14.979
-Come on.
-MARTIN: Banji.

19:15.023 --> 19:16.503
-BANJI: Hey, Martin.
-NATE: Look at that.

19:16.546 --> 19:18.026
[Martin speaks TshiVenda]

19:18.069 --> 19:19.984
-Oh, my gosh.
-MARTIN: This is amazing, man.

19:20.028 --> 19:21.551
Ah. It's perfect. Thank you.

19:21.595 --> 19:22.944
-Yeah.
-Nate, this is Banji.

19:22.987 --> 19:24.467
Banji, this is my friend Nate

19:24.511 --> 19:25.947
-and his daughters.
-Hi, Banji. -Hey, Nate.

19:25.990 --> 19:27.427
-I'm good. I'm good.
-These are my daughters.

19:27.470 --> 19:28.515
-This is Norah and Mare.
-Hello. -Hello. -Hey.

19:28.558 --> 19:29.907
Oh, my God. That's beautiful.

19:29.951 --> 19:31.735
-Yeah. [chuckles]
-MARE: Look.

19:31.779 --> 19:34.608
Banji tracks the movement of
the pride through the reserve.

19:34.651 --> 19:36.000
-Yeah.
-That's a great job.

19:36.044 --> 19:37.306
Hey, man. Thank you.

19:37.350 --> 19:40.396
And that up there
is the Nandi pride.

19:40.440 --> 19:42.181
-BANJI: Yep.
-MARTIN: It's named after that

19:42.224 --> 19:44.139
magnificent matriarch
in the middle there.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.793
NATE:
Wow.

19:45.836 --> 19:48.883
Yep, and the males are Kuda
and his brother Kawe.

19:48.926 --> 19:50.580
-NORAH and MARE: Kawe?
-Kawe?

19:50.624 --> 19:52.278
-Kawe. Kawe.
-NORAH and MARE: Kawe. Kawe.

19:52.321 --> 19:54.149
And are we, uh...
are we safe right here?

19:54.193 --> 19:55.585
[laughs]:
Oh, you're safe. You're safe.

19:55.629 --> 19:57.239
They just finished off
last night's kill.

19:57.283 --> 19:58.588
-Okay, good.
-BANJI: Yeah.

19:58.632 --> 20:00.199
-That is insane.
-We should go close...

20:00.242 --> 20:02.026
-[lion growling]
-[gasping]

20:02.070 --> 20:03.724
-MARTIN: Okay. It's all right.
-[laughing]: You're scared.

20:03.767 --> 20:05.247
You're okay. He's just letting
you know that he's there.

20:05.291 --> 20:06.596
NATE [laughing]:
You're scared. You got scared.

20:06.640 --> 20:08.381
See, the way it works
with lions is

20:08.424 --> 20:10.818
the females do the hunting,
the males protect the pride.

20:10.861 --> 20:12.254
Well, protect them from what?

20:12.298 --> 20:13.603
Usually from other lions.

20:13.647 --> 20:15.257
Any lion from
outside the family

20:15.301 --> 20:17.041
comes into their territory,

20:17.085 --> 20:19.305
Kuda and Kawe
will leap onto it,

20:19.348 --> 20:22.482
start ripping it apart
limb from limb or die trying.

20:22.525 --> 20:25.354
It's the law of the jungle,
guys.

20:25.398 --> 20:27.530
It's the only law
that matters out here.

20:27.574 --> 20:30.098
♪

20:30.141 --> 20:31.795
What kind of rifle is that?

20:31.839 --> 20:33.449
Oh, it's a trank rifle.

20:33.493 --> 20:35.190
You know, just in case.

20:35.234 --> 20:36.757
[chuckles]:
Hope we don't need it.

20:36.800 --> 20:38.106
Hopefully.

20:38.149 --> 20:39.238
Shall we do this?

20:39.281 --> 20:40.587
-Yep.
-All right.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.371
So you just, like,
put it there?

20:42.415 --> 20:44.243
-Okay, so the dart goes...
-All right, so they usually

20:44.286 --> 20:45.505
go after the smallest one,

20:45.548 --> 20:47.115
so you might want
to hang on to that.

20:47.158 --> 20:48.856
-What? Really?
-Just in case. No, I'm kidding.

20:48.899 --> 20:50.814
-No, you can't have this.
-MARTIN: You definitely can't.

20:50.858 --> 20:52.294
Wait, you're not going
out there, right?

20:52.338 --> 20:53.991
MARTIN:
Shh.

20:54.035 --> 20:55.428
-What is he doing?
-[chuckles]: He's gonna...

20:55.471 --> 20:56.690
He's gonna go.

20:56.733 --> 20:58.387
-Mare.
-What?

20:58.431 --> 21:00.041
-Where you going? -Just going
to take some pictures.

21:00.084 --> 21:01.695
NORAH: Why do you always
have to be such a daredevil?

21:01.738 --> 21:03.349
-Nothing's gonna happen.
-NATE: Mare, you're gonna be

21:03.392 --> 21:04.524
-the death of me. Come here.
-Wait, what's he doing?

21:04.567 --> 21:06.439
Just showing them
he's not afraid.

21:06.482 --> 21:08.354
He raised them
from cubs, actually.

21:08.397 --> 21:10.530
Sent them out to the wild
when they were still young.

21:10.573 --> 21:12.140
-MARTIN: Hey, boys.
-Wait.

21:12.183 --> 21:14.664
MARTIN:
I see you, boys.

21:14.708 --> 21:16.492
Hello, my boys.

21:16.536 --> 21:18.233
Hello.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.191
I see you there.

21:20.235 --> 21:22.411
Easy.

21:22.455 --> 21:24.674
Easy, easy.

21:24.718 --> 21:28.069
-[lion purring]
-[laughs] Okay.

21:28.112 --> 21:30.332
Ah. [chuckles]

21:30.376 --> 21:31.899
Who's a big boy, eh?

21:31.942 --> 21:33.335
[chuckles]

21:33.379 --> 21:34.771
Who's a big boy?

21:34.815 --> 21:37.339
[grunts, chuckles]

21:37.383 --> 21:39.167
Oh. Hey.

21:39.210 --> 21:40.516
Hey. Whoa. Okay.

21:40.560 --> 21:42.344
Easy, Kuda.
Don't play so rough.

21:42.388 --> 21:44.172
Don't play so rough, my boy.

21:44.215 --> 21:45.913
Don't play so rough.

21:45.956 --> 21:48.655
You also want some love?
You want some love, yeah.

21:48.698 --> 21:50.047
[chuckles]

21:50.091 --> 21:51.788
[panting]

21:51.832 --> 21:53.660
Hang on, hang on.
What's happened to...

21:53.703 --> 21:55.705
What's happened to your girl?

21:57.054 --> 21:58.969
What's wrong with Nandi?

21:59.013 --> 22:01.798
-Nandi?
-[lion moaning]

22:01.842 --> 22:03.452
You okay, my girl?

22:03.496 --> 22:05.715
-[snarls, hisses]
-Okay.

22:05.759 --> 22:07.804
Okay.

22:07.848 --> 22:09.415
Just coming a little closer.

22:09.458 --> 22:11.242
What's wrong with your paw,
girl?

22:11.286 --> 22:13.201
[hisses]

22:13.244 --> 22:14.463
Please, just a little bit
closer.

22:14.507 --> 22:15.899
Let me look at you.

22:15.943 --> 22:17.727
I just want to have a look.
Let me see.

22:17.771 --> 22:19.163
-[growling]
-Okay. All right.

22:19.207 --> 22:21.165
Okay, I'm going. I'm going.

22:22.428 --> 22:24.386
-Banji.
-Yeah?

22:25.605 --> 22:27.302
-She's got a wound on her paw.
-Ah.

22:27.346 --> 22:29.173
I think it's a bullet,
but I can't be sure.

22:29.217 --> 22:31.219
I've got to get in closer, but
that's not gonna happen now,

22:31.262 --> 22:33.221
so see if you can find a vet.

22:33.264 --> 22:36.006
Okay. There's just too many
[speaks TshiVenda] now.

22:36.050 --> 22:37.443
Yeah, probably, man.

22:37.486 --> 22:38.792
What is...
[repeats TshiVenda word]

22:38.835 --> 22:40.271
-Damn it.
-It's poachers.

22:40.315 --> 22:42.535
-Oh.
-Illegal hunters.

22:44.014 --> 22:45.886
-NORAH: That was really nice,
Uncle Martin. -See that?

22:45.929 --> 22:48.410
You always got to make
a show of yourself, huh?

22:48.454 --> 22:49.977
-You want to have a go?
-Me?

22:50.020 --> 22:51.282
-Yeah. -No.
-Go on, Dad.

22:51.326 --> 22:53.197
-Try it. Just once.
-Oh, no.

22:53.241 --> 22:55.025
You know, just hug a lion and,
uh, take a picture with Mare.

22:55.069 --> 22:56.766
[chuckles]
My dad's not much of a hugger.

22:56.810 --> 22:58.638
-No? -Nah. -What?
-More of a fist bumper.

22:58.681 --> 23:00.161
I am a hugger.

23:00.204 --> 23:02.206
Well, I'm gonna try
and get some help.

23:02.250 --> 23:04.426
-It was very nice to meet you.
-Very nice to meet you, too.

23:04.470 --> 23:06.297
-All right, Banji.
-All right, Nate.

23:06.341 --> 23:08.865
-Cheers, Banji.
-Uh, Dr. Nate, brother.

23:08.909 --> 23:10.214
[Nate chuckles]

23:10.258 --> 23:11.564
What happened out there?

23:11.607 --> 23:13.087
She wasn't too happy.

23:13.130 --> 23:14.828
Uh, it's the female.

23:14.871 --> 23:16.307
She's got wounded.

23:16.351 --> 23:17.787
-Wounded? How?
-[engine starts]

23:17.831 --> 23:19.354
Poachers.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.443
There's a Tsonga village
just up the road, guys.

23:21.487 --> 23:23.358
Do you mind
if we stop by there?

23:23.402 --> 23:25.012
-No. Let's do it.
-Just want to ask people

23:25.055 --> 23:27.231
-if they saw anything.
-Come on. -MARE: Let's go.

23:30.017 --> 23:31.758
So you think, uh,
maybe someone at the village

23:31.801 --> 23:33.194
might have seen what happened?

23:33.237 --> 23:34.848
Yeah. Seen something,
heard something.

23:34.891 --> 23:37.503
-[engine starts]
-Anything unusual, you know?

23:37.546 --> 23:39.374
So, you're sure
you don't want a lion hug?

23:39.418 --> 23:41.115
Last chance. Eh?

23:41.158 --> 23:43.770
-No, I'm good.
-All right. Good.

23:46.729 --> 23:48.252
MARTIN:
It's getting worse and worse.

23:48.296 --> 23:49.689
The poachers
used to just be after

23:49.732 --> 23:51.517
the elephants and the rhinos.

23:51.560 --> 23:53.649
Now they're actively
going after the lions.

23:53.693 --> 23:56.043
-Why?
-They sell the teeth,

23:56.086 --> 23:59.176
the claws, even the bones
on the black market.

23:59.220 --> 24:00.656
-That's horrible.
-Yeah.

24:00.700 --> 24:02.310
There's a market
for them now as well.

24:02.353 --> 24:04.312
The bones?

24:04.355 --> 24:06.227
-Well...
-I don't know, man.

24:06.270 --> 24:09.056
I mean, I-I've read about
the anti-poachers online,

24:09.099 --> 24:10.753
-and they said that...
-Stop it.

24:10.797 --> 24:12.276
-What?
-[Mare scoffs]

24:12.320 --> 24:13.887
You read about
the anti-poachers online?

24:13.930 --> 24:15.279
-Yes.
-Really?

24:15.323 --> 24:17.238
And what did it say, Norah?

24:17.281 --> 24:18.761
-Well...
-No, what did it say?

24:18.805 --> 24:20.633
Okay. Well, they said
that people have actually

24:20.676 --> 24:23.766
hunted down
and killed the poachers.

24:23.810 --> 24:26.029
I mean, y-you've heard
of stories like that,

24:26.073 --> 24:27.596
right, Uncle Martin?

24:27.640 --> 24:29.555
-Right?
-Um, yeah.

24:29.598 --> 24:31.774
NORAH:  So, are you some kind
of an anti-poacher?

24:31.818 --> 24:33.472
MARTIN:  I mean, we just...
we're just trying

24:33.515 --> 24:35.909
to protect the animals
in every sense.

24:35.952 --> 24:37.998
[birds squawking]

24:45.745 --> 24:47.834
♪

25:05.329 --> 25:09.333
Okay, so, guys, listen,
this is not a tourist village.

25:09.377 --> 25:11.074
Okay? It's a...

25:11.118 --> 25:13.337
It's an actual real place
where people live.

25:13.381 --> 25:15.078
NORAH:
Thank you.

25:16.602 --> 25:18.299
Please just be
as polite as possible.

25:18.342 --> 25:20.344
Maybe get a little drink
at the bar.

25:20.388 --> 25:22.651
-Hair of the dog?
-Oh, no.

25:22.695 --> 25:24.610
Mare, you can take pictures,

25:24.653 --> 25:26.829
-but just ask them first, okay?
-Okay.

25:26.873 --> 25:28.744
The Tsonga are some
of the most polite

25:28.788 --> 25:31.007
and kind people
you'll ever meet.

25:31.051 --> 25:32.879
They speak a type of Venda.

25:32.922 --> 25:34.837
Well, Mom was actually
teaching Norah and I.

25:34.881 --> 25:36.273
-Really?
-Before she died.

25:41.801 --> 25:43.367
Wow, you sound good.
I like that.

25:43.411 --> 25:45.326
[chuckles]:
Thanks, Dad.

25:47.676 --> 25:49.896
NATE:
Where is everybody?

25:49.939 --> 25:51.985
-Hello?
-Hello?

25:52.028 --> 25:53.900
Hello?

25:53.943 --> 25:56.032
[Martin calling out
in TshiVenda]

25:57.643 --> 25:59.340
-Hey, Norah. Look, Norah.
-[goats bleating]

25:59.383 --> 26:01.211
-There's goats.
-The fire's still hot.

26:01.255 --> 26:02.865
[bleating continues]

26:02.909 --> 26:04.998
MARE:
Hey there, buddy.

26:05.041 --> 26:07.087
Don't they look like,
uh, dalmatian dogs?

26:07.130 --> 26:08.784
-[Norah chuckles]
-MARE: Hey.

26:08.828 --> 26:10.351
-[camera clicks] -Mare,
you can't take pictures, Mare.

26:10.394 --> 26:12.483
-Doesn't matter.
-Mare, stop taking pictures.

26:12.527 --> 26:14.616
-Why?
-Stop. Stop. Just... Shh.

26:14.660 --> 26:16.139
They're so cute.

26:16.183 --> 26:17.837
Do you think Uncle Martin
kills poachers?

26:17.880 --> 26:19.534
What do you think,
Miss Know-It-All?

26:19.578 --> 26:21.710
But that's what the article
said anti-poachers do.

26:21.754 --> 26:23.190
Come on. Norah!

26:23.233 --> 26:25.061
-What?
-You can't just wander off.

26:25.105 --> 26:26.715
Come on.

26:26.759 --> 26:28.238
Does that frighten you?

26:28.282 --> 26:29.892
No. [scoffs]

26:29.936 --> 26:32.199
I have a rainbow of emotions
at my disposal, Mare.

26:32.242 --> 26:33.679
Well, you look scared
to me, Norah.

26:33.722 --> 26:36.203
-I'm not scared, Mare.
-Uh-huh.

26:36.246 --> 26:38.292
NATE:
Hey, guys. Don't walk off.

26:38.335 --> 26:40.033
Just stay close.

26:40.076 --> 26:42.078
All right?

26:42.122 --> 26:43.732
Hey, Martin.

26:43.776 --> 26:46.735
Let's, uh...
let's get out of here, okay?

26:46.779 --> 26:48.607
MARTIN:
Yeah, okay.

26:49.782 --> 26:51.174
Jesus. Hang on, hang on.

26:51.218 --> 26:52.698
-Nate, go back to the girls.
-What?

26:52.741 --> 26:54.395
Go back to the girls right now.

26:54.438 --> 26:56.310
-Don't let them come in here.
-[flies buzzing]

26:57.398 --> 26:58.878
-NORAH: Dad, what is it?
-MARE: Dad, what's going on?

26:58.921 --> 27:01.315
Uh, it's okay.
Just, uh, stay close, okay?

27:03.883 --> 27:05.667
Martin?

27:05.711 --> 27:07.190
[flies buzzing]

27:07.234 --> 27:10.019
Oh, my God. Jesus Christ.

27:12.935 --> 27:14.937
Guys, you got to, uh...
you got to go.

27:14.981 --> 27:16.591
-You can't see, okay?
-What's wrong?

27:16.635 --> 27:18.158
I just need you to walk away
for a second, okay?

27:18.201 --> 27:19.942
-I'll be right there.
-Okay.

27:19.986 --> 27:21.378
[goat bleating]

27:21.422 --> 27:23.424
What happened in here?

27:23.467 --> 27:25.818
MARTIN:
I have no idea, man.

27:28.734 --> 27:31.301
Jesus Christ.
Some of them are my friends.

27:32.825 --> 27:35.305
Shit. What did this?

27:35.349 --> 27:38.091
Only thing that makes any sense
is a lion, but...

27:38.134 --> 27:39.962
-cats don't do this, you know?
-What?

27:40.006 --> 27:41.703
Lions don't do this.

27:41.747 --> 27:45.359
I've heard stories, but no lion
that I've ever seen.

27:45.402 --> 27:47.578
Any alive over there?

27:47.622 --> 27:49.102
No.

27:49.145 --> 27:50.843
Oh, shit.

27:50.886 --> 27:52.888
Most of this village
is women and kids, bro.

27:52.932 --> 27:55.021
Think the rest of them
got away? Huh?

27:55.064 --> 27:57.371
I hope so.

27:57.414 --> 27:59.373
Okay, this is... this is bad.

27:59.416 --> 28:00.766
With this much blood,

28:00.809 --> 28:02.332
there should be
hyenas around already.

28:02.376 --> 28:04.595
What does that mean?

28:04.639 --> 28:07.381
It means that
whatever did this is...

28:07.424 --> 28:09.339
Still out there? Huh?

28:09.383 --> 28:11.602
I'm gonna get the gun.
Go get the girls.

28:11.646 --> 28:12.995
Okay. Uh, Mare!

28:13.039 --> 28:14.344
-Dad.
-We got to go.

28:14.388 --> 28:16.259
Norah. Where is your sister?

28:16.303 --> 28:18.044
She was playing with the goats.

28:18.087 --> 28:19.610
-Where is she?
-I don't know.

28:19.654 --> 28:21.308
Norah? Well, she-she...

28:21.351 --> 28:22.918
-Where's Norah?
-Dad, she was just behind me.

28:22.962 --> 28:24.441
What do you mean,
she was just...

28:24.485 --> 28:25.965
-Norah, come on!
-Norah, we got to go, baby!

28:26.008 --> 28:27.401
Let's go!

28:27.444 --> 28:29.055
-Norah!
-Mare, where is she?

28:29.098 --> 28:30.709
I don't know if she's hid...
I don't know where she...

28:30.752 --> 28:32.101
-What are you talking... Norah!
-Norah!

28:32.145 --> 28:33.973
Hey! Norah, we got to go!

28:34.016 --> 28:35.278
Norah, come on!

28:35.322 --> 28:36.758
You had one job, Mare.

28:36.802 --> 28:38.194
That's all.
Look after your sister.

28:38.238 --> 28:40.370
-Norah!
-Norah, come on!

28:40.414 --> 28:42.024
-Hey, Norah!
-Norah!

28:42.068 --> 28:43.939
Go check over there.
Go check over there.

28:43.983 --> 28:45.462
-Norah!
-Norah!

28:45.506 --> 28:47.334
Norah, can you hear me?

28:47.377 --> 28:49.249
[Norah screams]

28:50.990 --> 28:53.209
-MARE: Norah!
-NATE: Norah!

28:54.602 --> 28:55.777
-NORAH: Mare, please!
-NATE: Hey.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.039
-[Norah gasping]
-MARE: Norah!

28:57.083 --> 28:58.519
NATE:
Can you hear me?

28:58.562 --> 29:00.086
[Norah gasping]

29:00.129 --> 29:01.914
Shit.

29:01.957 --> 29:04.264
Norah!

29:04.307 --> 29:06.788
-Where you at?
-NORAH: Dad!

29:06.832 --> 29:08.790
Hey, hey, hey, hey. Hey, baby.

29:08.834 --> 29:10.270
You okay? You okay?
Are you hurt?

29:10.313 --> 29:11.619
-Are you hurt? Huh?
-[gasping, whimpering]

29:11.662 --> 29:12.925
Look at me, look at me. Okay.

29:12.968 --> 29:15.188
-NORAH: She got...
-[flies buzzing]

29:15.231 --> 29:17.320
♪

29:21.368 --> 29:24.197
Banji, do you copy? We've got
a situation in the village.

29:24.240 --> 29:26.112
MARE: Norah, don't worry.
We're gonna be fine. Norah.

29:26.155 --> 29:27.678
Banji, Banji, come in.

29:27.722 --> 29:29.376
It's Martin.
Are you still in the field?

29:29.419 --> 29:30.551
Hey, Norah.

29:30.594 --> 29:31.900
Hey, Norah, it's gonna be okay.

29:31.944 --> 29:33.772
Ah, it's not gonna work.

29:33.815 --> 29:36.905
The mountain blocks
the CB radio signal.

29:36.949 --> 29:39.429
There's a seasonal outpost
about six K's up the road here,

29:39.473 --> 29:41.692
so I'm just gonna go down there
and call it in.

29:41.736 --> 29:43.825
I can't...
Dad, I want to go home.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.261
No, we're gonna go home,
all right?

29:45.305 --> 29:47.133
Call whoever you got to
when we get back.

29:47.176 --> 29:49.309
Listen, there's like 15
families in that village, okay?

29:49.352 --> 29:50.658
I know some of those people.

29:50.701 --> 29:52.094
I'm not gonna
leave them out here.

29:52.138 --> 29:54.444
Do you think there's anybody
still alive?

29:54.488 --> 29:55.881
-NATE: I don't know.
-[man yells]

29:55.924 --> 29:57.447
-Hey, what's that?
-MAN: Please!

29:57.491 --> 29:59.014
-NATE: Hold up. Slow down.
-Help me!

29:59.058 --> 30:01.625
-NATE: Slow down. Slow down.
-[man yells]

30:01.669 --> 30:04.628
Okay, guys,
just stay in the car.

30:04.672 --> 30:06.761
[man shouting in TshiVenda]

30:06.805 --> 30:08.241
-Wait, what?
-NATE: It's okay.

30:08.284 --> 30:10.896
-What's he doing?
-It's okay. It's all right.

30:10.939 --> 30:12.680
-MARTIN: Mutende.
-NATE: Hey, Martin.

30:12.723 --> 30:14.247
One second, girls.

30:14.290 --> 30:16.205
-MARTIN: How many lions? Lions.
-MARE: It's okay.

30:16.249 --> 30:18.207
MARTIN:
How many? [speaks TshiVenda]

30:18.251 --> 30:20.122
He's from the village.
He needs help.

30:20.166 --> 30:21.776
Keep the girls in the car.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.212
[Norah and Mare gasping,
whimpering]

30:23.256 --> 30:24.735
-Are you okay? Is he okay?
-What's going on?

30:24.779 --> 30:26.346
He'll be fine.
Just stay in the car.

30:26.389 --> 30:27.826
-Is he gonna be okay?
-Okay? Just stay in the car.

30:27.869 --> 30:29.131
MARTIN:
Just-just-just... just hold on.

30:29.175 --> 30:31.612
-Hey.
-[Martin speaking TshiVenda]

30:33.048 --> 30:34.963
-His name is Mutende.
-NATE: Okay.

30:35.007 --> 30:37.531
-And he-he went with
a couple other guys... -Okay.

30:37.574 --> 30:39.315
-...to try to take it out, like
I thought. -Hey, man. Okay.

30:39.359 --> 30:41.013
-It got his brother as well.
-You got a aid kit?

30:41.056 --> 30:42.884
Yeah, there's one in the...
there's one in the car.

30:42.928 --> 30:44.451
-[Mutende speaking TshiVenda]
-[Nate repeats TshiVenda word]

30:44.494 --> 30:45.713
-Okay. What's he saying?
-[repeats TshiVenda word]

30:45.756 --> 30:47.106
-It means "devil."
-Devil. Okay.

30:47.149 --> 30:48.847
-All right, M-Mutende...
-[rustling nearby]

30:48.890 --> 30:50.370
All right, just relax, okay?

30:50.413 --> 30:51.893
[birds squawking]

30:51.937 --> 30:53.460
-Hey, what is it?
-Shh.

30:53.503 --> 30:55.244
-Hey.
-Shh, shh, shh, shh.

30:55.288 --> 30:56.985
-Hey, Martin. Come back.
-Go back to the girls.

30:57.029 --> 30:59.553
-[animal moans, pants]
-Hey, buddy, come here, okay?

30:59.596 --> 31:01.381
-Nate, go back to the car.
-Just relax, okay?

31:01.424 --> 31:03.383
All right, we just got to get
this guy out of here.

31:03.426 --> 31:05.341
Okay. Just stay here, okay?
I'll be right back.

31:05.385 --> 31:07.517
[repeatedly whispering
TshiVenda word]

31:07.561 --> 31:08.823
-NORAH: Dad.
-Where's the medical kit?

31:08.867 --> 31:10.346
-Where's the medical kit?
-Wha-What?

31:10.390 --> 31:11.870
-What? Was it a lion?
-Martin said there was

31:11.913 --> 31:13.001
-a medical kit in here.
Where is it? -Dad!

31:13.045 --> 31:14.611
-What?
-Was it a lion?

31:14.655 --> 31:16.004
-Be quiet.
-Yes. Okay?

31:16.048 --> 31:17.527
-NORAH: Wha... [whimpers]
-Now, just relax.

31:17.571 --> 31:19.529
-Dad, what's going on?
-Okay. All right. No, no.

31:19.573 --> 31:21.575
-NORAH: Lions? [gasping]
-Uncle Martin's out there.

31:21.618 --> 31:23.577
-Um, see if you can...
-Yes, Norah.

31:23.620 --> 31:25.144
...find someone on the radio.

31:25.187 --> 31:26.449
Okay, but Martin said that
we're out of range here.

31:26.493 --> 31:27.886
I don't care what Martin said.
Try.

31:27.929 --> 31:29.365
-Okay, but, Dad, what do I say?
-Okay?

31:29.409 --> 31:30.801
Dad, what do I say? Dad!

31:30.845 --> 31:32.542
-Um, just tell them that...
-Dad, what...

31:32.586 --> 31:34.370
Tell them that we're outside
Tsonga village, all right?

31:34.414 --> 31:35.894
-Tsonga village. Okay.
-Two miles on the road.

31:35.937 --> 31:37.939
We got a injured male.
Tell them...

31:37.983 --> 31:39.288
-Just don't panic, okay?
-Okay.

31:39.332 --> 31:40.420
[Norah gasping]

31:40.463 --> 31:41.638
-NORAH: Mare.
-Okay, uh...

31:41.682 --> 31:43.727
MARE:
Hello? Hello?

31:43.771 --> 31:45.077
They're gonna answer.

31:45.120 --> 31:46.948
Help. Can someone hear me?

31:46.992 --> 31:48.558
Help.
Can somebody please hear me?

31:48.602 --> 31:50.082
NATE:
Hey, man. Hey.

31:50.125 --> 31:51.866
Hey. You okay?

31:53.172 --> 31:55.914
Oh, come on, now.
Hang in there. Hang in there.

31:58.873 --> 32:01.571
Come on. Come on.

32:01.615 --> 32:03.704
♪

32:07.186 --> 32:10.015
-[insects trilling]
-[birds chirping]

32:14.280 --> 32:16.456
[whispers]:
Come on.

32:16.499 --> 32:18.588
♪

32:39.392 --> 32:40.741
[gasps quietly]

32:42.047 --> 32:44.005
-Okay. It's okay.
-[snapping sound in distance]

32:44.049 --> 32:46.094
[gasps] What was that?

32:46.138 --> 32:48.096
[breathing heavily]

32:52.971 --> 32:55.016
[birds screeching]

32:57.062 --> 32:59.107
♪

33:11.554 --> 33:14.209
-[water splashing]
-[quiet growling]

33:18.300 --> 33:20.389
♪

33:34.577 --> 33:36.579
[animal moans nearby]

33:41.323 --> 33:43.630
[animal growling]

33:46.241 --> 33:48.591
[footsteps splashing]

34:06.348 --> 34:07.915
[animal growls]

34:07.958 --> 34:10.439
-[yelps]
-[gunshot]

34:10.483 --> 34:12.528
Martin!

34:16.315 --> 34:18.143
Hey!

34:27.239 --> 34:28.936
Hey!

34:37.118 --> 34:39.033
NORAH:
Dad, come back!

34:40.774 --> 34:42.950
-Okay.
-Dad!

34:42.993 --> 34:44.517
-Okay, I'm gonna go outside.
Just... -Wait, Mare. Please.

34:44.560 --> 34:46.214
-No, just stay. Just stay
right... -Please. Mare!

34:46.258 --> 34:48.086
-Please! Don't leave me!
-Stay. Just breathe. It's okay.

34:48.129 --> 34:50.218
-MARE: Norah, I'm right here.
-Hey, man.

34:50.262 --> 34:52.568
You up here?

34:52.612 --> 34:54.309
Huh?

34:54.353 --> 34:56.050
Martin!

34:57.182 --> 34:58.748
[animal growling]

34:58.792 --> 35:00.794
Shit. Get in the car!

35:00.837 --> 35:02.926
-Get in the car now!
-Dad!

35:05.233 --> 35:07.235
[animal growling]

35:09.803 --> 35:11.674
Whoa. Whoa!

35:14.199 --> 35:16.766
-You guys okay? You guys okay?
-[Norah and Mare whimpering]

35:16.810 --> 35:18.812
[Norah and Mare screaming]

35:18.855 --> 35:21.206
Norah, stay down. Stay down.

35:21.249 --> 35:23.077
[growling]

35:23.121 --> 35:25.514
Stay down.
Stay down. Stay down.

35:25.558 --> 35:28.256
[Norah and Mare whimpering,
panting]

35:28.300 --> 35:29.823
[whispering]:
Stay down. Stay down.

35:29.866 --> 35:32.086
It's okay. It's okay.

35:32.130 --> 35:34.088
-[snarling, growling]
-[screaming]

35:34.132 --> 35:36.046
Get over there, Mare!
Get over there!

35:36.090 --> 35:38.223
[gasping, grunting]

35:38.266 --> 35:40.138
NATE:
Get...

35:40.181 --> 35:42.183
Take the wheel!

35:42.227 --> 35:44.403
-Take the wheel, Mare!
-[engine revving]

35:44.446 --> 35:46.753
[grunting]

35:46.796 --> 35:49.016
Drive! Drive!

35:50.017 --> 35:51.410
Watch out! Watch out!

35:51.453 --> 35:52.759
Don't hit the man!

35:52.802 --> 35:55.762
[Norah and Mare gasping,
screaming]

35:58.765 --> 36:00.854
-[steam hissing]
-[all panting]

36:03.030 --> 36:04.814
NATE:
Okay. Okay.

36:04.858 --> 36:07.165
Hey. Hey, Mare. Mare.

36:07.208 --> 36:08.688
Mare, you okay? Come here.

36:08.731 --> 36:10.124
Come here. Look at me.

36:10.168 --> 36:11.517
-Did you hurt yourself, huh?
-NORAH: Dad.

36:11.560 --> 36:13.780
-Where's the lion?
-Okay.

36:13.823 --> 36:16.826
Hey. Hey, Norah. Norah.
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

36:16.870 --> 36:19.960
-Breathe. Breathe. Slow down.
-[taking deep breaths]

36:20.003 --> 36:21.701
Like that. There you go.
That's it.

36:21.744 --> 36:23.311
You're doing good. Doing good.

36:23.355 --> 36:25.835
Okay, baby, I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

36:25.879 --> 36:28.142
What the hell just happened?

36:30.275 --> 36:32.320
Is it still out there?

36:34.975 --> 36:36.542
MARE:
Be careful. Don't cut yourself.

36:36.585 --> 36:39.066
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Just-just stay right there.

36:40.328 --> 36:42.156
NORAH: The lion really
smashed out that window.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.245
-Move over.
-What happened to Uncle Martin?

36:44.289 --> 36:45.986
NATE:
Ow! Oh, my leg.

36:46.029 --> 36:47.901
It got me good.

36:47.944 --> 36:50.033
We got to go get
some help, okay?

36:50.077 --> 36:51.687
[engine whining, sputtering]

36:51.731 --> 36:53.254
Come on, come on,
come on, come on,

36:53.298 --> 36:55.213
come on, come on, come...

36:55.256 --> 36:58.172
Come on, come on, come on.

36:58.216 --> 37:00.609
-Are we trapped here?
-No.

37:00.653 --> 37:03.873
No, Norah,
we're not trapped here, okay?

37:03.917 --> 37:05.310
Someone will find us.

37:05.353 --> 37:07.181
-Someone will come by.
-We don't know that.

37:07.225 --> 37:09.052
Uncle Martin said that
this part of the reserve

37:09.096 --> 37:10.576
is closed to the public.

37:10.619 --> 37:12.839
And the radio
is just static, Dad.

37:12.882 --> 37:15.189
-Do we even know where we are?
-Mare.

37:15.233 --> 37:16.843
-Do we know where we...
-Mare! Come on.

37:16.886 --> 37:19.149
-Just stop, okay? Just stop.
-[Mare whimpering]

37:19.193 --> 37:20.934
Guys?

37:20.977 --> 37:23.676
What-what if
that thing isn't gone?

37:23.719 --> 37:25.460
-It could still be out here.
-Hey. Hey, hey, hey, hey.

37:25.504 --> 37:27.070
-No, she's right.
-Wait. No, no, no, no, no.

37:27.114 --> 37:29.421
No, but we didn't get
very far, Dad.

37:29.464 --> 37:31.118
It could still be out there.

37:31.161 --> 37:32.424
[static crackling over radio]

37:32.467 --> 37:34.034
MARTIN [over radio]:
Nate, come in.

37:34.077 --> 37:35.688
-Whoa. What is that, now? Wait.
-[Martin groans]

37:35.731 --> 37:37.298
-Can you hear the radio?
-MARTIN: Nate, can you hear me?

37:37.342 --> 37:38.821
Can you hear it?

37:38.865 --> 37:40.214
Oh.

37:40.258 --> 37:42.172
-Hey, Martin.
-Nate, I can hear you.

37:42.216 --> 37:43.696
-Can you... can you hear me?
-Hey. Yes.

37:43.739 --> 37:45.611
Yes, we hear you.

37:46.829 --> 37:48.309
Do you copy?

37:48.353 --> 37:50.311
Yes, N-Nate, I copy you.

37:50.355 --> 37:51.878
I copy you.

37:51.921 --> 37:53.749
What happened, man?
Did you get attacked?

37:53.793 --> 37:56.535
[grunts] I'm, uh...

37:56.578 --> 37:59.451
-I'm in a bad way, bro.
-[flies buzzing]

37:59.494 --> 38:01.061
NATE:
You're in a bad way?

38:01.104 --> 38:03.977
What happened?
What kind of condition you in?

38:04.020 --> 38:06.284
The lion...

38:06.327 --> 38:09.417
The lion, uh, just came
out of nowhere, you know?

38:09.461 --> 38:12.768
And, um, I can't stand.

38:12.812 --> 38:14.857
Um, my leg's, uh...

38:14.901 --> 38:16.859
My leg's torn up.

38:16.903 --> 38:18.600
I'm losing too much blood.

38:18.644 --> 38:20.341
I think I'm gonna pass out.

38:20.385 --> 38:21.908
Are the girls okay?

38:21.951 --> 38:23.779
-And M-Mutende, is he okay?
-Yeah.

38:23.823 --> 38:26.086
Yeah, look, no, Mutende, he...
he didn't make it, okay?

38:26.129 --> 38:27.957
He didn't make it,
but the girls are okay.

38:28.001 --> 38:29.611
We're here. We're okay.

38:29.655 --> 38:33.006
-And, um, the truck... the...
-[engine sputtering]

38:33.049 --> 38:35.835
It's dead, man. Um...

38:35.878 --> 38:38.490
Hey, man, I don't know
what to do right now.

38:38.533 --> 38:40.753
Okay? I don't know what to do.

38:40.796 --> 38:44.017
Okay, you-you want to just,
um, stay there.

38:44.060 --> 38:45.888
Someone will come.

38:45.932 --> 38:48.935
And, uh, stay in the car.

38:48.978 --> 38:51.894
I'm-I'm seeing...
I'm seeing, uh, st...

38:53.156 --> 38:56.072
Whew. I'm seeing stars, man,
feeling dizzy.

38:56.116 --> 38:57.770
Hey, Martin, listen to me.

38:57.813 --> 39:01.077
Um, you're gonna go into shock,
all right?

39:01.121 --> 39:02.601
I need you to stop
the bleeding.

39:02.644 --> 39:03.906
-Mare, is he okay?
-Yeah. He's gonna be okay.

39:03.950 --> 39:05.343
Needless to say, all right?

39:05.386 --> 39:06.996
I need you to take
your belt off, uh...

39:07.040 --> 39:08.737
uh, wrap it around your leg,

39:08.781 --> 39:11.436
and I need you to pull
that shit tight.

39:11.479 --> 39:14.830
I did that already, but, um,
it's not really helping.

39:14.874 --> 39:16.528
I've... I...
He went really deep, man.

39:16.571 --> 39:18.181
It's all the way to the bone.

39:18.225 --> 39:20.096
Y-You did that? Okay. Okay.

39:20.140 --> 39:21.881
Um, do you have
your lighter on you?

39:21.924 --> 39:23.361
That Zippo?

39:23.404 --> 39:25.493
Uh, yeah, yeah. Yes.

39:25.537 --> 39:27.408
You got that?
All right, do me a favor.

39:27.452 --> 39:29.018
Take your knife out, all right?

39:29.062 --> 39:30.846
You're not gonna like me
for this, man,

39:30.890 --> 39:33.675
but I need you to heat that
knife as hot as it can get.

39:33.719 --> 39:35.416
It needs to be
as hot as Hades, man.

39:35.460 --> 39:37.113
Then you need to put it
on the artery.

39:37.157 --> 39:38.854
All right? And you need
to lay it on there

39:38.898 --> 39:40.290
while it's really hot.

39:40.334 --> 39:41.640
All right?
We're gonna stop the bleeding.

39:41.683 --> 39:42.945
How much time?
We need to go get him.

39:42.989 --> 39:44.207
Hold on, Mare. Hold on.

39:44.251 --> 39:46.079
And how's that doing?
Is it hot?

39:46.122 --> 39:47.428
Yeah.

39:47.472 --> 39:48.647
All right, tell me
when it's done, man.

39:48.690 --> 39:49.822
Come on,
tell me when it's done.

39:49.865 --> 39:51.867
[sizzling]

39:54.435 --> 39:56.611
Okay, I'm gonna go for it.

39:57.960 --> 39:59.962
-[sizzling]
-[screaming]

40:00.006 --> 40:01.442
[Martin screaming in distance]

40:01.486 --> 40:02.748
-Hey, man, I heard you.
-NORAH: He's okay.

40:02.791 --> 40:04.445
I actually heard you.

40:04.489 --> 40:06.447
You're close by.

40:06.491 --> 40:08.971
So listen, um...

40:09.015 --> 40:11.844
I'm gonna try
and come to you, okay?

40:11.887 --> 40:13.715
Is he okay?

40:13.759 --> 40:15.543
Do you understand that, Martin?
I'm gonna try and come to you.

40:15.587 --> 40:17.066
-Where is he?
-MARTIN: Uh... [groans]

40:17.110 --> 40:18.328
Dad, here. He's probably...

40:18.372 --> 40:20.243
MARTIN:
N-Negative, Nate.

40:20.287 --> 40:23.333
Um, I'm not alone.

40:23.377 --> 40:24.813
Uh, what?

40:25.814 --> 40:27.468
He's staring right at me.

40:27.512 --> 40:29.383
NATE: The lion is staring
right at you?

40:29.427 --> 40:31.472
-MARE: Oh, my God.
-NATE: Why would he do that?

40:31.516 --> 40:33.213
MARE: Okay, Dad,
we have to go get him.

40:33.256 --> 40:34.736
NATE:
Hold on.

40:34.780 --> 40:38.044
The son of a bitch
is staring right at me.

40:38.087 --> 40:39.828
-MARE: Dad, we have to go
and get him now. -[growling]

40:39.872 --> 40:41.308
NATE:
That doesn't sound right, man.

40:41.351 --> 40:42.657
What's going on?

40:42.701 --> 40:45.225
Dude, that doesn't sound,
uh, natural.

40:46.531 --> 40:50.186
If I didn't know any better,
I'd say I'm the bait.

40:51.536 --> 40:53.668
NATE:
We-we got to come get you, man.

40:53.712 --> 40:56.366
If you stay by there,
you're gonna die.

40:56.410 --> 40:58.412
MARE:
Dad, he's gonna bleed out.

40:58.456 --> 41:00.501
NATE:
We gonna figure this out.

41:00.545 --> 41:03.504
MARE:
We can't leave him out there.

41:03.548 --> 41:06.202
You don't understand.

41:06.246 --> 41:08.466
We're in his territory now.

41:08.509 --> 41:10.685
Okay, Martin, just listen.
Just sit tight, okay?

41:10.729 --> 41:12.470
I got to think
about this, okay?

41:12.513 --> 41:14.820
Wait, Dad,
what about the trank rifle?

41:15.951 --> 41:17.605
-Where is it? Go find it.
Go find it. -Yeah. -Uh...

41:17.649 --> 41:19.041
-Martin, I can't leave you
out there, buddy. -Okay. Okay.

41:19.085 --> 41:20.652
-No way.
-I don't see anything.

41:20.695 --> 41:22.131
-Do you see it? -No. I don't.
-No, but I know...

41:22.175 --> 41:23.785
You don't see it? Hold up.

41:23.829 --> 41:25.439
Let me get back there.
Norah, just move over there.

41:25.483 --> 41:27.093
-Oh, uh, Dad, your leg.
-Just move over there.

41:27.136 --> 41:29.138
-Wait, wait, wait. Dad.
-Just move over there, okay?

41:29.182 --> 41:30.792
Wait. Dad!

41:30.836 --> 41:32.315
-What?
-Listen to me.

41:32.359 --> 41:34.492
-Your leg, it is torn up.
-My leg's what? Ah, shit.

41:34.535 --> 41:35.928
It's not that bad.

41:35.971 --> 41:37.320
It's all right. It's stopped.

41:37.364 --> 41:38.974
-Okay.
-It's just superficial, okay?

41:39.018 --> 41:40.846
-It's all right. Do you see it?
-No, don't see it.

41:40.889 --> 41:42.804
-No? What about this box?
Check this box. -[Norah groans]

41:42.848 --> 41:44.502
-NORAH: It-it-it's locked.
-NATE: It's locked?

41:44.545 --> 41:45.981
-Dang it.
-Um, see...

41:46.025 --> 41:47.287
Hey, see if there's
a key right in there.

41:47.330 --> 41:48.897
-No, it's just the one.
-Nothing?

41:48.941 --> 41:50.812
-Uh, check the glove box
real quick. -Okay.

41:50.856 --> 41:53.293
-Um...
-[rummaging]

41:53.336 --> 41:55.513
MARE [sighs]: There's nothing
in the glove box.

41:55.556 --> 41:57.210
-NATE: Hold on.
-NORAH: It's not loosening.

41:57.253 --> 41:58.559
[Nate grunts]

41:58.603 --> 41:59.734
-MARE: Oh, God.
-NATE: Whew!

41:59.778 --> 42:01.170
-Are you okay?
-You all good?

42:01.214 --> 42:02.302
-Yeah, I'm good.
-Okay. Good job, good job.

42:02.345 --> 42:04.347
-Get it.
-Watch your fingers.

42:05.610 --> 42:07.786
-Now, what's the plan? Um...
-NORAH: Okay, uh...

42:07.829 --> 42:09.962
NATE:
We got, uh... That's it.

42:10.005 --> 42:12.138
Dad, uh, do you know how
to put that thing together?

42:12.181 --> 42:13.748
-No, I have no idea.
-I know how.

42:13.792 --> 42:15.576
How do you know how
to put it together?

42:15.620 --> 42:17.360
Because I-I paid attention when
Banji assembled it earlier.

42:17.404 --> 42:19.188
-It can't be that hard.
-Did you, now?

42:19.232 --> 42:20.625
How does that go? All right,
so you know how to use this?

42:20.668 --> 42:22.191
-Uh, no.
-To use that, press that button

42:22.235 --> 42:23.497
only when you're talking,
all right?

42:23.541 --> 42:24.977
-Okay, okay.
-So, where does this go?

42:25.020 --> 42:26.282
-What did Banji say?
-Make sure the numbers...

42:26.326 --> 42:27.545
Dad, make sure the numbers
go there.

42:27.588 --> 42:29.198
-Right here?
-Yeah.

42:29.242 --> 42:30.722
-Hey, Martin, can you hear me?
-And then screw it.

42:30.765 --> 42:32.506
Screw it in right here?
Martin, can you hear me?

42:32.550 --> 42:34.116
-[static crackling over radio]
-Are you still there?

42:34.160 --> 42:36.249
-MARTIN: I'm here.
-Whew. Okay, good.

42:36.292 --> 42:38.120
We have the, um...
the trank rifle.

42:38.164 --> 42:40.166
If we shoot this thing,
it might just buy us

42:40.209 --> 42:42.472
-some time to come get you.
-No. No, no, no.

42:42.516 --> 42:44.474
That's a...
That's a terrible idea.

42:44.518 --> 42:45.911
-That's...
-[flies buzzing]

42:45.954 --> 42:48.435
We got to try. Okay?

42:48.478 --> 42:50.611
MARTIN:
The lion's moved off.

42:50.655 --> 42:52.657
I do not have eyes on the lion.

42:52.700 --> 42:54.180
He's wandered off.

42:54.223 --> 42:55.442
-What?
-What?

42:55.485 --> 42:57.400
MARTIN:
Stay in the vehicle.

42:57.444 --> 42:59.402
♪

42:59.446 --> 43:01.491
NATE: Martin, we don't have
a choice right now.

43:01.535 --> 43:03.232
It's the best we can do.

43:03.276 --> 43:05.060
You-you're only gonna have
one shot, man,

43:05.104 --> 43:07.236
but if-if you...

43:07.280 --> 43:11.197
if you can hit it, it should
buy us a couple hours, yeah.

43:11.240 --> 43:13.329
I got it. W-We're not gonna
leave you there, okay?

43:13.373 --> 43:14.635
We just can't do that.

43:14.679 --> 43:16.332
You want to...
you want to get...

43:16.376 --> 43:17.986
You want to get
somewhere high, you know?

43:18.030 --> 43:19.727
-NATE: Open the sunroof.
-NORAH: Okay.

43:19.771 --> 43:21.511
-Dad, no, you got to...
-No, no, no, no. Not that one.

43:21.555 --> 43:23.209
-No, guys! Wait, wait.
-Can you just stop touching it?

43:23.252 --> 43:24.166
Please stop touching.
Just stay in the car, okay?

43:24.210 --> 43:25.907
Okay.

43:25.951 --> 43:27.517
All right, be careful.

43:27.561 --> 43:29.650
-Okay, okay.
-Dad.

43:31.478 --> 43:34.220
-MARE: Be careful up there.
-NORAH: Please.

43:34.263 --> 43:36.352
NATE: Stay away
from the broken window.

43:36.396 --> 43:38.920
♪

43:38.964 --> 43:40.748
All right. Pass me that gun.

43:40.792 --> 43:42.358
-MARE: You got it?
-Yeah.

43:42.402 --> 43:44.056
Okay.

43:45.231 --> 43:47.189
[panting]

43:47.233 --> 43:48.713
-NORAH: Are you good?
-All right.

43:48.756 --> 43:50.236
-Get Martin on the radio.
-Okay.

43:50.279 --> 43:52.542
Ask him, uh,
what I'm supposed to look for.

43:52.586 --> 43:54.109
What should he be looking for?

43:54.153 --> 43:57.896
MARTIN: Movement.
Anything that casts a shadow.

43:57.939 --> 44:00.289
-What? What'd he say?
-MARE: Look for the shadows.

44:00.333 --> 44:01.726
-Shadows? Um...
-Shadows, yeah.

44:01.769 --> 44:03.292
NORAH:
Like a shadow moving.

44:03.336 --> 44:04.685
Okay. Um...

44:04.729 --> 44:06.339
MARE:
It's just a bunch of shadows.

44:07.906 --> 44:09.429
-NATE: Uh...
-NORAH: Do you see anything?

44:09.472 --> 44:10.865
No, I don't see...

44:17.263 --> 44:18.917
-NORAH: Dad, do you see it?
-Hold on.

44:18.960 --> 44:20.745
Hold on. Hold on.

44:20.788 --> 44:22.834
[rustling]

44:26.054 --> 44:27.969
[panting]

44:28.013 --> 44:29.318
No.

44:29.362 --> 44:30.755
MARE: Ask him where he is
or something.

44:30.798 --> 44:32.452
Ask him for
a landmark near him.

44:32.495 --> 44:34.410
Something else, something I...
something I can see.

44:34.454 --> 44:36.064
NORAH: Is there any landmark
that he can find?

44:36.108 --> 44:38.458
Anything to find you.
Where are you?

44:42.070 --> 44:43.855
Can he see the hunter's blind?

44:43.898 --> 44:45.291
-NATE: What'd he say?
-What's a hunter's blind?

44:45.334 --> 44:46.814
He said look for
a hunter's blind.

44:46.858 --> 44:48.033
Hunter's blind?
What does that look like?

44:48.076 --> 44:49.512
MARE:
What does it look like?

44:49.556 --> 44:50.644
MARTIN:
It's the only man-made thing...

44:50.688 --> 44:52.080
It's on stilts.

44:52.124 --> 44:53.952
The only man-made thing
on stilts, Dad.

44:53.995 --> 44:56.041
Uh...

44:56.084 --> 44:57.912
Hold on. I don't see it.

44:57.956 --> 44:59.392
I don't see it.

44:59.435 --> 45:00.741
NORAH:
I don't see anything.

45:00.785 --> 45:02.743
NATE:
Uh...

45:02.787 --> 45:04.136
I don't see it. Uh...

45:04.179 --> 45:05.267
-No, I don't see...
Do you see it? -Dad!

45:05.311 --> 45:07.052
Dad, Dad, it's right there!

45:07.095 --> 45:08.662
-Where? -NATE: Where? Where?
-It's right over there, Dad.

45:08.706 --> 45:09.881
-Can you see it? R-Right there.
-I don't see it.

45:09.924 --> 45:11.578
-Where?
-NORAH: I don't see it.

45:11.621 --> 45:13.275
-NATE: Hold on. I see it.
-NORAH: Where are you going?

45:13.319 --> 45:14.755
-NATE: Stop moving the car!
-Where are you... Mare!

45:14.799 --> 45:16.278
-Stop rocking the...
-Where are you going?

45:16.322 --> 45:17.758
-Mare! -Mare, what the hell
are you doing?

45:17.802 --> 45:19.325
I'm gonna check
if I can see Uncle Martin.

45:19.368 --> 45:20.892
-Get back in the car right now.
-Mare! Mare!

45:20.935 --> 45:22.676
No, we have to do something,
or he's gonna die.

45:22.720 --> 45:23.938
-I'm not going anywhere. I'm...
-NORAH: Mare, come back!

45:23.982 --> 45:25.331
NATE: I'll do it!
Get back in the car!

45:25.374 --> 45:26.071
MARE: I'm gonna check
if I can see him.

45:26.114 --> 45:26.724
Mare! I'll go!

45:26.767 --> 45:27.899
[panting]

45:27.942 --> 45:29.422
NATE:
Mare, I said I'll go!

45:29.465 --> 45:30.902
NORAH:
Dad! It's here! It's here!

45:30.945 --> 45:32.860
-[lion growls]
-Run, Mare!

45:32.904 --> 45:34.470
-Get away from the car now!
-NORAH: Here!

45:34.514 --> 45:36.255
-Pass me another! Quick!
Pass it! Quick! -Here!

45:36.298 --> 45:37.604
-Here, Dad! Take it!
-Toss it.

45:37.647 --> 45:39.040
[growls]

45:39.084 --> 45:40.389
[Nate yells]

45:40.433 --> 45:41.913
-[grunts]
-NORAH: Dad!

45:41.956 --> 45:43.479
[lion roars]

45:43.523 --> 45:45.307
NATE:
Stay away, Mare!

45:45.351 --> 45:48.180
-[snarling]
-Hey!

45:52.445 --> 45:54.012
NORAH:
Dad, are you okay?

45:54.055 --> 45:56.014
Dad! Dad!

45:56.057 --> 45:58.494
-[Nate grunting]
-[lion snarling]

46:02.498 --> 46:04.674
NORAH:
Dad, please answer me!

46:06.589 --> 46:08.287
Please, Dad!

46:08.330 --> 46:10.289
[Norah gasping, whimpering]

46:10.332 --> 46:11.681
-[snarling]
-[Norah screams]

46:11.725 --> 46:13.771
[Nate grunting]

46:16.991 --> 46:19.254
NORAH: Dad, look,
the gun is on the other side.

46:19.298 --> 46:20.734
It's right there.

46:20.778 --> 46:22.736
-Dad, he's coming!
-[growling]

46:22.780 --> 46:24.825
[Nate grunting]

46:31.832 --> 46:33.529
-NATE: No, no. Norah!
-[Norah screaming]

46:33.573 --> 46:35.531
Get away from the window!
Stay in the back!

46:35.575 --> 46:37.533
NORAH: Dad, please help!
He's on the car!

46:37.577 --> 46:39.622
Dad!

46:39.666 --> 46:41.799
[growls]

46:43.626 --> 46:46.499
Dad, get the gun. Dad, grab it!

46:46.542 --> 46:48.066
Hurry up!

46:48.109 --> 46:50.416
[snarling]

46:55.464 --> 46:57.466
-Uncle Martin.
-MARTIN: I'm here. I'm here.

46:57.510 --> 46:58.859
I'm coming.

46:58.903 --> 47:00.905
[panting]

47:03.124 --> 47:05.039
-Are you okay?
-Mare, what are you doing here?

47:05.083 --> 47:06.998
Don't worry. I'm gonna get you
back to the cruiser, okay?

47:07.041 --> 47:08.434
I told you to stay in the car.

47:08.477 --> 47:10.175
I'm gonna get you back,
Uncle Martin.

47:17.399 --> 47:19.445
-[Nate grunts]
-[snarling]

47:19.488 --> 47:21.534
[Nate grunting]

47:26.539 --> 47:28.236
[grunting]

47:29.281 --> 47:30.891
-[grunts]
-[lion roars in pain]

47:30.935 --> 47:32.545
[panting]

47:37.637 --> 47:39.900
-Dad, are you okay?
-Yeah. Yeah. You okay?

47:39.944 --> 47:42.250
-Yeah. Yes.
-Is it gone? Huh?

47:42.294 --> 47:44.731
-Is it gone?
-Yeah, it's gone. Yeah.

47:44.774 --> 47:47.168
-Are you okay?
-[panting]

47:47.212 --> 47:48.691
[Norah whimpers]

47:49.910 --> 47:51.738
[lion moans softly]

47:51.781 --> 47:53.740
Okay. Okay. You okay?

47:53.783 --> 47:55.394
-Yeah.
-All right. Good job.

47:55.437 --> 47:56.961
-Good job. Good job.
-Thank you.

47:57.004 --> 47:59.050
Close the window. Okay?
Close the window.

48:01.008 --> 48:02.749
Hey, Mare!

48:02.792 --> 48:04.098
Mare, come back!

48:04.142 --> 48:06.318
Hey, Mare, can you hear me?

48:07.623 --> 48:09.538
I'll get your sister, okay?
Stay right there.

48:09.582 --> 48:11.192
Hey, Mare, can you hear me?

48:11.236 --> 48:12.541
Dad? Norah?

48:12.585 --> 48:13.847
-Shh.
-Okay.

48:13.891 --> 48:14.979
-NATE: Hey, Mare, come in.
-Okay.

48:15.022 --> 48:17.416
Martin, you okay?

48:17.459 --> 48:19.026
Yeah, we're fine.
Are you guys okay?

48:19.070 --> 48:20.332
What happened to the lion?

48:20.375 --> 48:22.334
Your sister stuck a dart
in his ass.

48:22.377 --> 48:23.596
MARE:
She did?

48:23.639 --> 48:25.859
NATE:
Yeah, she sure did.

48:25.903 --> 48:28.601
Okay. Well, we're almost there,
and we're okay.

48:28.644 --> 48:31.343
Come on. One, two... Go ahead.

48:31.386 --> 48:33.214
[yelling]

48:33.258 --> 48:34.476
-Okay.
-It's okay.

48:34.520 --> 48:36.652
-It's okay, Uncle Martin.
-Okay.

48:36.696 --> 48:38.045
-I think I got it.
-It's okay.

48:38.089 --> 48:39.568
I think I got it. Hey, Mare.

48:39.612 --> 48:41.744
Uh, Mare, can you pass
the tweezers right there?

48:41.788 --> 48:43.398
-Uh-huh. Which one?
-I need... Yep, yep, that one.

48:43.442 --> 48:44.965
I want you to clamp this
right here.

48:45.009 --> 48:46.358
Hold on tight
and do not let go.

48:46.401 --> 48:48.012
Do you understand?

48:48.055 --> 48:49.535
All right. Uh, Norah,
can you check in that box--

48:49.578 --> 48:51.363
the aid box-- if they got
some sutures in there?

48:51.406 --> 48:52.973
Can you tell me what they got?

48:53.017 --> 48:55.149
-Uh, there's, uh, nylon...
-What do they have?

48:55.193 --> 48:57.586
-...silk and polypropylene.
-Okay, man.

48:57.630 --> 48:59.371
Okay, give me
a 16-millimeter silk.

48:59.414 --> 49:01.155
-Um, there's 3/0
18-millimeter silk. -Good job.

49:01.199 --> 49:03.157
All right, it's not perfect
but will do.

49:03.201 --> 49:05.159
-Are your hands clean?
-Definitely not.

49:05.203 --> 49:06.856
Take a-a alcohol swab,
wipe your hands,

49:06.900 --> 49:08.946
and then, uh,
pass the, uh, suture packet

49:08.989 --> 49:10.686
with the needle up, okay?

49:10.730 --> 49:12.819
-Okay.
-NATE: Okay, Mare. You okay?

49:12.862 --> 49:14.212
-All right.
-MARE: He's bleeding out a lot.

49:14.255 --> 49:15.691
It's gonna be all...
I know. I know.

49:15.735 --> 49:17.215
Just relax, okay?
How you doing, Norah?

49:17.258 --> 49:18.999
Okay.

49:19.043 --> 49:20.348
All right, he's gonna pass out
in a second, all right?

49:20.392 --> 49:22.002
-He's gonna be all right.
All right? -Yeah.

49:22.046 --> 49:23.134
There you go.
No, turn it around.

49:23.177 --> 49:24.657
Turn it around for me.

49:24.700 --> 49:26.006
Good job.

49:26.050 --> 49:27.442
-All right.
-Okay.

49:27.486 --> 49:30.228
-[exhales] Okay. Okay.
-[Mare groans]

49:34.101 --> 49:36.408
[Mare shudders]

49:36.451 --> 49:37.931
All right.

49:39.106 --> 49:42.109
I got it. I got it. I got it.
I got it. I got it.

49:44.459 --> 49:46.374
-Okay, you can let go.
-Okay.

49:46.418 --> 49:48.028
-Guys. Guys.
-Did a good job, okay?

49:48.072 --> 49:50.335
-Good job.
-What about the lion?

49:50.378 --> 49:51.814
Martin said the tranquilizer

49:51.858 --> 49:53.555
would keep him out
for a couple of hours.

49:53.599 --> 49:55.035
We'll be long gone by then.

49:55.079 --> 49:56.732
But it's the same lion,
isn't it?

49:56.776 --> 49:59.126
The one that killed all
those people in the village?

50:00.214 --> 50:02.303
It has to be.

50:03.478 --> 50:06.046
Norah, are you sure you put
a dart in that thing?

50:06.090 --> 50:07.308
-What?
-Oh, God.

50:07.352 --> 50:08.875
NORAH:
Yes. Oh, my gosh.

50:08.918 --> 50:11.138
[Norah whimpering]

50:11.182 --> 50:13.140
-Yes.
-Oh, my God.

50:13.184 --> 50:16.274
MARE: Dad, the tranquilizer's
wearing off already.

50:16.317 --> 50:17.927
All right. Don't panic, okay?

50:17.971 --> 50:20.234
MARE: I thought
he'd be out for hours.

50:20.278 --> 50:22.367
♪

50:24.108 --> 50:26.153
[lion grunting softly]

50:39.732 --> 50:41.690
[moaning]

50:50.177 --> 50:52.223
[insects chirping]

50:54.877 --> 50:57.054
MARE: Hello?
Is anyone out there? Over.

50:57.097 --> 50:58.620
Please, we need help.

50:58.664 --> 51:02.798
If anyone can hear me,
someone please answer.

51:02.842 --> 51:04.713
Guys, we got to consider
that we're gonna be

51:04.757 --> 51:07.542
in this vehicle for a while,
all right? So...

51:07.586 --> 51:09.762
Cruiser's dead, and as long
as that thing is out there,

51:09.805 --> 51:11.590
we got to conserve this water.

51:11.633 --> 51:13.461
How much do we have?

51:13.505 --> 51:16.116
Well, um, you got one there.

51:16.160 --> 51:18.075
Uh, whatever's in
these four bottles for now.

51:18.118 --> 51:19.859
-Dad, this is not enough.
-I know, but it's gonna

51:19.902 --> 51:21.469
-have to last till tomorrow.
-No, not for four people.

51:21.513 --> 51:22.862
It's gonna have to last
till tomorrow.

51:22.905 --> 51:24.168
Tomorrow?

51:24.211 --> 51:25.647
Hey, someone's gonna
come find us.

51:25.691 --> 51:27.345
I promise you, okay?

51:27.388 --> 51:29.782
-Don't make another promise
you can't keep. -Hey.

51:29.825 --> 51:31.088
What are you talking about?

51:31.131 --> 51:33.046
How about the time
you took Norah

51:33.090 --> 51:35.135
on that carriage ride
and you promised her that

51:35.179 --> 51:36.876
-our mother wasn't gonna die?
-What?

51:36.919 --> 51:39.096
-No, that's not fair.
-Norah came home that night,

51:39.139 --> 51:41.141
and she was happy,
and she held my hands

51:41.185 --> 51:42.664
and she assured me
that our mother

51:42.708 --> 51:44.144
was gonna be okay
because you promised.

51:44.188 --> 51:45.928
NORAH: Mare, will you just
shut the hell up

51:45.972 --> 51:47.930
-for one God dang second,
please? -NATE: That's not fair.

51:47.974 --> 51:49.410
-Norah, he... -All right.
-All you ever do is talk.

51:49.454 --> 51:51.978
Okay, guys. [sighs]

51:52.021 --> 51:54.067
Just stop for a second, okay?

51:54.111 --> 51:56.243
-Come on, Mare.
-Hey. Norah, look at me.

51:56.287 --> 51:57.636
I'm sorry, Dad.

51:57.679 --> 51:59.028
Norah, don't be sorry.

51:59.072 --> 52:00.769
NORAH:
I cannot believe you right now.

52:07.994 --> 52:11.215
I always thought you guys
would get back together.

52:11.258 --> 52:13.347
♪

52:15.828 --> 52:17.612
I did, too.

52:25.142 --> 52:26.665
[sniffles]

52:26.708 --> 52:28.275
I'm sorry.

52:34.151 --> 52:35.239
[insects chirping]

52:35.282 --> 52:37.806
[Martin coughs, clears throat]

52:37.850 --> 52:39.678
NATE:
Hey.

52:39.721 --> 52:42.724
Tell me that I'm home in bed.

52:42.768 --> 52:44.770
You're home in bed, man.

52:44.813 --> 52:47.207
Warm, comfortable.

52:47.251 --> 52:49.644
-See, here's some water.
-[groans]

52:49.688 --> 52:51.994
Promise. Just relax.

52:52.038 --> 52:53.692
Don't do too much.

52:53.735 --> 52:55.389
There you go.
There you go, man.

52:55.433 --> 52:57.870
[pained grunting]

53:02.918 --> 53:04.703
[grunts]

53:04.746 --> 53:06.357
The girls okay?

53:06.400 --> 53:09.534
-Yeah.
-[Martin groans, exhales]

53:09.577 --> 53:11.362
Thank God.

53:11.405 --> 53:13.407
What happened with the lion?

53:14.669 --> 53:16.932
Tranquilizer didn't seem
to affect it much,

53:16.976 --> 53:20.240
but I haven't seen it
since before dark.

53:20.284 --> 53:22.068
MARTIN:
Mm.

53:22.111 --> 53:23.983
Maybe it gave up.

53:25.289 --> 53:27.682
Maybe.

53:27.726 --> 53:30.294
Maybe not.

53:30.337 --> 53:33.079
It's, uh...

53:33.122 --> 53:35.777
Everybody knows that
a wounded lion is dangerous,

53:35.821 --> 53:38.215
but I've never seen
anything like this.

53:39.303 --> 53:44.046
Multiple attacks
without eating its prey.

53:44.090 --> 53:46.223
Attacking a vehicle.

53:46.266 --> 53:48.399
Lions don't do that.

53:48.442 --> 53:52.794
It's like he-he...
he knows who his real enemy is.

53:53.795 --> 53:55.232
Meaning what?

53:55.275 --> 53:57.364
[sighs]
The poachers, you know?

53:57.408 --> 53:59.627
They take out the lions,

53:59.671 --> 54:02.239
they split up the prides,
and then...

54:03.675 --> 54:06.199
Well...

54:06.243 --> 54:08.201
now they're fighting back.

54:08.245 --> 54:12.640
This lion's gone rogue
because they killed his pride,

54:12.684 --> 54:16.296
and now he's coming
after all of us.

54:16.340 --> 54:18.255
[sighs]

54:19.560 --> 54:21.823
[whispers]: I've got to get
my girls out of here.

54:21.867 --> 54:23.521
MARTIN:
Mmm.

54:24.478 --> 54:26.654
Hmm. [groans]

54:26.698 --> 54:28.961
The radio don't work.

54:29.004 --> 54:31.659
We ain't got no water.

54:31.703 --> 54:35.184
Look, man, I can't...
I can't help you.

54:35.228 --> 54:37.099
Barely feel my leg.

54:37.143 --> 54:39.406
You can't go out there
on your own.

54:39.450 --> 54:41.713
You're miles from anywhere.

54:41.756 --> 54:44.890
The best thing you can do
is stay here

54:44.933 --> 54:47.893
and wait for help to come.

54:47.936 --> 54:50.287
You go out there
without a weapon,

54:50.330 --> 54:52.114
it'll be you versus him,

54:52.158 --> 54:55.161
and that is not a fight
that you are designed to win.

54:58.164 --> 55:01.515
[takes deep breath]

55:01.559 --> 55:04.736
You're doing right
by these girls today.

55:04.779 --> 55:07.347
Amahle would be proud of you.

55:10.394 --> 55:13.135
♪

55:24.973 --> 55:27.062
♪

55:28.542 --> 55:31.458
NATE:
Don't go. Don't go.

55:34.679 --> 55:37.725
[inhales sharply, sniffs]

55:37.769 --> 55:39.814
[grunts]

55:42.077 --> 55:44.079
[objects clattering]

55:49.302 --> 55:51.086
Hey.

55:51.130 --> 55:53.219
You guys drink the water?

55:53.262 --> 55:55.656
Why you got to drink the...

55:55.700 --> 55:58.224
Mare. Mare.

55:58.267 --> 56:00.357
Norah. Norah.

56:00.400 --> 56:02.359
Hey, Martin. Martin.

56:02.402 --> 56:04.012
Where are the...
Where are the girls?

56:04.056 --> 56:05.492
Hey. Hey.

56:05.536 --> 56:07.451
Girls. Hey.

56:08.452 --> 56:10.018
What...

56:12.543 --> 56:14.240
Hey.

56:14.283 --> 56:16.111
Mare! Norah!

56:17.461 --> 56:19.637
Shit. What the...

56:19.680 --> 56:21.421
Mare!

56:21.465 --> 56:22.857
-Hey, girls!
-[Norah and Mare scream]

56:22.901 --> 56:24.468
Oh!

56:24.511 --> 56:26.600
♪

56:37.089 --> 56:39.004
AMAHLE:
Nathaniel.

56:41.310 --> 56:42.790
Nathaniel.

56:42.834 --> 56:44.749
NATE:
I need you. I need you near me.

56:44.792 --> 56:46.881
-I need you.
-Are you okay?

56:50.537 --> 56:52.191
Amahle.

56:52.234 --> 56:54.106
Are you okay?

57:10.862 --> 57:12.690
-Mare.
-MARE: Hmm?

57:12.733 --> 57:14.518
What's wrong?

57:15.736 --> 57:17.825
I loved your mom.

57:17.869 --> 57:19.697
Okay?

57:20.872 --> 57:24.136
I loved her with
everything I had to give.

57:24.179 --> 57:25.920
I promise you.

57:27.792 --> 57:29.837
It just wasn't working.

57:32.971 --> 57:35.364
I thought I had more time.

57:36.540 --> 57:38.585
Thought I could solve it.

57:41.196 --> 57:44.983
Now every time I look at you,
I see so much of her in you.

57:47.725 --> 57:51.337
I need you to forgive me.

57:53.861 --> 57:55.820
Can you do that?

57:59.867 --> 58:01.913
[TshiVenda chatter over radio]

58:01.956 --> 58:03.436
What was that?

58:03.480 --> 58:05.699
I don't know.
You turn the radio on?

58:05.743 --> 58:07.745
I never... I never
turned it off. It just...

58:07.788 --> 58:09.529
But, Dad,
maybe somebody heard me.

58:09.573 --> 58:11.662
-Maybe it's a rescue party.
-Let me turn it up. Hold on.

58:11.705 --> 58:13.664
Hold on. Hold up.
[clears throat]

58:13.707 --> 58:15.796
-Can you hear 'em? Uh...
-[TshiVenda chatter continues]

58:15.840 --> 58:17.537
-Are they saying something?
-MARTIN: What did he say?

58:17.581 --> 58:19.408
Hey, copy. Do-do you hear us?

58:19.452 --> 58:21.585
-Tell them where we are.
-I'm trying. Uh...

58:21.628 --> 58:23.369
-[horn honking] -Can't make out
what they're saying.

58:23.412 --> 58:25.458
-MAN [on radio]: Kees.
-Hey, copy. Can you hear us?

58:25.502 --> 58:27.504
-Hey.
-[vehicle approaching]

58:28.983 --> 58:30.681
Is that them?

58:30.724 --> 58:32.334
Is that...

58:32.378 --> 58:33.814
I think they heard.

58:33.858 --> 58:35.250
[chatter in TshiVenda]

58:35.294 --> 58:37.078
MARE:
Dad, they've got guns.

58:37.122 --> 58:39.124
-NORAH: Why do they have guns?
-NATE: Oh, they're poachers.

58:39.167 --> 58:40.647
-Oh, God.
-They're poachers, all right?

58:40.691 --> 58:42.823
Whatever happens,
just stay in the vehicle.

58:42.867 --> 58:44.259
[chatter in TshiVenda]

58:44.303 --> 58:46.610
Hey. Just stay
in the vehicle, okay?

58:46.653 --> 58:48.742
[chatter continues
in TshiVenda]

58:52.224 --> 58:53.834
NATE:
Hey.

58:53.878 --> 58:55.662
-Hey, what's up? Uh...
-Hey, hey. Wait, wait.

58:55.706 --> 58:58.360
Uh, hey. Hold on.
Hey, hey. Hold on, man.

58:58.404 --> 59:00.885
-You hold on. You hold on.
-Okay. Okay.

59:00.928 --> 59:02.582
[chatter continues
in TshiVenda]

59:02.626 --> 59:04.323
Hey, what's up?
We need some help, okay?

59:04.366 --> 59:06.020
We-we-we were attacked,
and we need some help.

59:06.064 --> 59:07.326
-You're American.
-Yeah.

59:07.369 --> 59:08.762
Long way from home, American.

59:08.806 --> 59:10.111
Yeah. Uh, look,
my friend's in a bad...

59:10.155 --> 59:11.460
-Who are they?
-Those are my daughters.

59:11.504 --> 59:12.810
Those are my two daughters,
okay?

59:12.853 --> 59:14.594
And, uh, my friend
is in a bad way.

59:14.638 --> 59:16.030
He needs some help right now.

59:16.074 --> 59:17.597
-Um...
-You shouldn't be out here.

59:17.641 --> 59:19.512
-It's a very dangerous place.
-No, I know that.

59:19.556 --> 59:22.297
And, um, I was attacked,
and I'm telling you, man,

59:22.341 --> 59:24.561
I just need a ride out of here.
That's all.

59:24.604 --> 59:26.388
-Attacked by what?
-A lion.

59:26.432 --> 59:28.565
It was huge. It took out
the-the whole village.

59:28.608 --> 59:30.828
That's the big male
that got away.

59:30.871 --> 59:32.569
He's from the pride
that we killed last night.

59:32.612 --> 59:34.179
Hey, excuse me. Hey. Hey.

59:34.222 --> 59:36.050
Hey, we need to all
get out of here, okay?

59:36.094 --> 59:37.399
When last have you seen
this lion?

59:37.443 --> 59:38.618
I don't know.
It was like t-two hours.

59:38.662 --> 59:39.924
Brother, brother,
can I pay you?

59:39.967 --> 59:41.403
-H-H-Hey.
-Brother, can I pay you?

59:41.447 --> 59:43.144
-Not brother of yours, man.
-No, no, no.

59:43.188 --> 59:44.842
I'm just saying, you...
you guys are poachers, right?

59:44.885 --> 59:46.321
-We can take American dollars.
-We're not poachers.

59:46.365 --> 59:48.106
All right, I won't say...
Hey, man.

59:48.149 --> 59:49.760
You got to put that down, okay?
Those are my daughters.

59:49.803 --> 59:51.544
-Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!
-No, no, no, no. Just relax.

59:51.588 --> 59:53.502
-You can take American dollars?
-Yes, I-I got...

59:53.546 --> 59:55.722
-I can pay you. Yes.
-5,000 American dollars.

59:55.766 --> 59:57.942
Yes, I got you, okay?
All right?

59:57.985 --> 59:59.421
[chatter in TshiVenda]

59:59.465 --> 1:00:00.814
We need to unload the cargo

1:00:00.858 --> 1:00:02.511
before we get
to the village, eh?

1:00:02.555 --> 1:00:04.339
NATE:
Um, thank you. I appreciate it.

1:00:04.383 --> 1:00:06.037
And I won't say a word.

1:00:06.080 --> 1:00:07.691
You say there are three inside,
including your friend?

1:00:07.734 --> 1:00:09.997
-Yeah. Just, uh...
-NORAH: Dad, what's happening?

1:00:10.041 --> 1:00:12.260
NATE: They're gonna help us
get out of here.

1:00:13.435 --> 1:00:15.394
KEES:
What the hell is this?

1:00:15.437 --> 1:00:16.961
-Whoa, whoa! What the...
-NORAH: Dad!

1:00:17.004 --> 1:00:18.745
-KEES: I know this man.
-Hey, hey! Hey, relax!

1:00:18.789 --> 1:00:20.442
-Okay, okay. It's all right,
baby. -He's an anti-poacher!

1:00:20.486 --> 1:00:22.314
Hey, what are you doing, man?
Put the gun down.

1:00:22.357 --> 1:00:24.142
-Put the gun down.
-He killed three of my men.

1:00:24.185 --> 1:00:26.318
Okay, man. Just relax, okay?
Just relax. All right?

1:00:26.361 --> 1:00:27.798
[Kees speaks TshiVenda]

1:00:27.841 --> 1:00:29.451
-Hey, don't touch her! [grunts]
-NORAH: Dad!

1:00:29.495 --> 1:00:31.279
-MARE: No! No, no, no, no!
-KEES: Keep him there!

1:00:31.323 --> 1:00:34.152
-KEES: Stay down!
-[Mare and Norah screaming]

1:00:34.195 --> 1:00:36.415
-Let her go.
-[lion growling]

1:00:36.458 --> 1:00:38.286
Stop! Stop! Stop!

1:00:38.330 --> 1:00:39.810
It's coming!

1:00:39.853 --> 1:00:42.073
-[snarls]
-[screaming]

1:00:42.116 --> 1:00:44.162
[frantic yelling]

1:00:44.205 --> 1:00:46.817
NATE:
Norah! Norah, come here!

1:00:46.860 --> 1:00:48.775
Come here! Okay. Okay.

1:00:48.819 --> 1:00:50.690
All right, let's get
out of here. Come on.

1:00:50.734 --> 1:00:52.170
Get in!

1:00:53.562 --> 1:00:55.695
Get in. You okay?
Mare, you okay?

1:00:55.739 --> 1:00:57.741
All right. Here's our chance
to get out of here, okay?

1:00:57.784 --> 1:00:59.307
Get the water.
Get the medical supplies.

1:00:59.351 --> 1:01:01.092
I'm gonna get that truck,
I'm gonna back it up,

1:01:01.135 --> 1:01:02.963
and we're gonna put
Uncle Martin in it, all right?

1:01:03.007 --> 1:01:04.443
-Okay. Okay.
-It's okay, stay here.

1:01:04.486 --> 1:01:06.750
MARE: It's okay.
You're gonna get help, okay?

1:01:06.793 --> 1:01:09.883
-[frantic chatter in TshiVenda]
-[gunfire]

1:01:11.232 --> 1:01:13.278
[engine revving]

1:01:19.937 --> 1:01:22.896
No. Come on.
No, no, no, no, no!

1:01:22.940 --> 1:01:24.419
[grunts]

1:01:24.463 --> 1:01:26.552
[panting]

1:01:31.775 --> 1:01:33.820
[gunfire]

1:01:35.387 --> 1:01:36.693
-There's no keys.
-What happened?

1:01:36.736 --> 1:01:37.911
One of them's got the keys.

1:01:37.955 --> 1:01:39.739
-What?
-I got to go get the keys.

1:01:39.783 --> 1:01:42.437
-NORAH: Dad, you don't know
how to hot-wire a car? -No.

1:01:42.481 --> 1:01:44.918
I do not know
how to hot-wire a car.

1:01:44.962 --> 1:01:46.572
I went to medical school.

1:01:46.615 --> 1:01:47.834
Well, you should've
double-majored or something.

1:01:47.878 --> 1:01:49.444
The guy in the yellow shirt,

1:01:49.488 --> 1:01:51.185
he was driving--
I got to find him.

1:01:51.229 --> 1:01:52.839
-He must have the keys.
-NORAH: Dad, please don't go.

1:01:52.883 --> 1:01:55.276
That truck is the only way
we can get out of here.

1:01:55.320 --> 1:01:57.322
-No. -He must've gone
that way, all right?

1:01:57.365 --> 1:01:58.671
He couldn't have gone far.
You heard the gunshots.

1:01:58.715 --> 1:02:00.673
-They were close.
-No. I don't like it.

1:02:00.717 --> 1:02:02.066
Mare, I'm not asking you
to like it.

1:02:02.109 --> 1:02:03.241
I'm asking you
to look after Norah

1:02:03.284 --> 1:02:04.372
and look after Uncle Martin.

1:02:04.416 --> 1:02:05.809
All right? Can you do that?

1:02:05.852 --> 1:02:07.462
I've got the walkie.
I'll be ten minutes.

1:02:07.506 --> 1:02:08.855
-MARE: Okay.
-That's all.

1:02:08.899 --> 1:02:10.378
Please, Daddy.
You cannot get hurt.

1:02:10.422 --> 1:02:12.206
-You have to be careful.
-Hey, what's my name?

1:02:12.250 --> 1:02:13.512
Supersize Nugget Nate.

1:02:13.555 --> 1:02:14.556
That's right.

1:02:14.600 --> 1:02:15.862
Nate, Nate. Get his gun.

1:02:15.906 --> 1:02:18.256
Okay. All right.

1:02:18.299 --> 1:02:20.432
-Ten minutes.
-MARE: Be careful.

1:02:22.869 --> 1:02:24.741
NORAH [whispers]:
Dad, please be careful.

1:02:24.784 --> 1:02:26.830
♪

1:02:34.838 --> 1:02:36.883
[panting]

1:02:43.672 --> 1:02:45.544
[whispers]:
Hey.

1:02:47.807 --> 1:02:50.636
Oh. I need them keys, man.

1:02:52.594 --> 1:02:54.858
-[gunshot]
-[lion growls]

1:03:04.781 --> 1:03:07.609
[man wheezing]

1:03:13.659 --> 1:03:15.661
[man speaking TshiVenda]

1:03:30.894 --> 1:03:32.939
[panting]

1:03:34.854 --> 1:03:36.856
[footsteps splashing]

1:03:44.690 --> 1:03:46.735
[lion growling softly]

1:03:49.826 --> 1:03:51.436
[gasps softly]

1:03:56.833 --> 1:03:59.052
[loud rattling]

1:04:04.231 --> 1:04:06.190
[shuddering breaths]

1:04:06.233 --> 1:04:07.931
-[static crackles]
-MARE [over radio]: Dad? Dad?

1:04:07.974 --> 1:04:09.889
[Nate muttering frantically]

1:04:09.933 --> 1:04:12.109
MARE:
Dad, can you hear us?

1:04:12.152 --> 1:04:13.893
[muffled]:
Dad?

1:04:15.895 --> 1:04:17.549
Dad, say something, please.

1:04:17.592 --> 1:04:19.986
Oh, please, Dad. Please.

1:04:20.030 --> 1:04:21.596
Dad?

1:04:21.640 --> 1:04:23.163
[over radio]:
Can you hear me?

1:04:23.207 --> 1:04:25.252
Dad, say something, please.

1:04:26.427 --> 1:04:28.603
Dad, can you hear me?

1:04:28.647 --> 1:04:30.127
[growls softly]

1:04:30.170 --> 1:04:31.519
[static crackles]

1:04:31.563 --> 1:04:33.608
[lion growling over radio]

1:04:43.836 --> 1:04:45.882
♪

1:05:06.772 --> 1:05:08.861
[snake hissing]

1:05:17.478 --> 1:05:20.220
-[snake hisses]
-[lion growling]

1:05:27.358 --> 1:05:29.186
NORAH [sighs]:
Mare, do you see him?

1:05:29.229 --> 1:05:30.927
-MARE: No. -Well, it's been
ten minutes already.

1:05:30.970 --> 1:05:32.754
MARE:
I know, Norah.

1:05:32.798 --> 1:05:34.191
Mare, y-you know, we should
try him on the walkie again.

1:05:34.234 --> 1:05:35.932
We can't, Norah.
He's not responding.

1:05:35.975 --> 1:05:37.716
What? I mean, we've got to do
something, Mare.

1:05:37.759 --> 1:05:39.761
-I know we have...
-[both scream]

1:05:39.805 --> 1:05:42.895
-[speaking TshiVenda]
-[Mare and Norah whimpering]

1:05:44.418 --> 1:05:46.507
-What?
-What?

1:05:47.900 --> 1:05:49.815
Mare, don't let him in, please.

1:05:49.858 --> 1:05:52.296
-[door banging]
-Mare, you can't.

1:05:52.339 --> 1:05:53.906
Mare, please.

1:05:53.950 --> 1:05:55.908
[both gasping]

1:05:55.952 --> 1:05:57.823
Look at his...

1:06:00.782 --> 1:06:03.089
-Is Dad okay?
-[man speaking TshiVenda]

1:06:03.133 --> 1:06:05.483
[rustling in bushes]

1:06:08.573 --> 1:06:11.793
Mare, where did he go?

1:06:12.794 --> 1:06:15.362
[bird calling in distance]

1:06:15.406 --> 1:06:17.495
♪

1:06:27.026 --> 1:06:29.072
[lion moans]

1:06:41.214 --> 1:06:43.390
[creaking]

1:06:55.489 --> 1:06:56.925
[horn honking in distance]

1:06:58.318 --> 1:07:00.190
-[horn honking]
-Dad, please come back. Please.

1:07:00.233 --> 1:07:02.627
[honking continues]

1:07:02.670 --> 1:07:05.021
-[creaking]
-[lion growling softly]

1:07:06.544 --> 1:07:08.633
[honking continues]

1:07:26.694 --> 1:07:28.783
♪

1:07:43.146 --> 1:07:45.191
[gasping weakly]

1:07:56.159 --> 1:07:58.161
[man groaning weakly]

1:08:03.514 --> 1:08:05.472
NATE:
Sorry about this, man.

1:08:18.181 --> 1:08:20.313
[whispering]:
Hey. It's me.

1:08:20.357 --> 1:08:22.663
-Can you hear me?
-[static crackling]

1:08:22.707 --> 1:08:24.578
NORAH [gasps]:
Dad, is that you?

1:08:24.622 --> 1:08:26.102
Copy, copy. I made it.

1:08:26.145 --> 1:08:27.668
I made it. I'm here.

1:08:27.712 --> 1:08:29.148
[sighs]

1:08:29.192 --> 1:08:31.455
I got the keys.
I'm coming back, okay?

1:08:31.498 --> 1:08:33.413
I'm coming back.

1:08:37.896 --> 1:08:39.941
♪

1:08:52.215 --> 1:08:54.260
[panting]

1:09:02.877 --> 1:09:04.444
[Martin coughs]

1:09:04.488 --> 1:09:06.011
MARE:
Are you okay?

1:09:06.054 --> 1:09:07.360
Here, Uncle Martin.

1:09:07.404 --> 1:09:08.753
Have some water.

1:09:10.450 --> 1:09:12.365
Thanks.

1:09:12.409 --> 1:09:14.193
Mmm.

1:09:14.237 --> 1:09:15.760
[exhales sharply, sniffs]

1:09:15.803 --> 1:09:17.501
Here.

1:09:18.763 --> 1:09:20.373
-What? What's wrong?
-[window squeaking]

1:09:20.417 --> 1:09:22.506
-[Norah gasps]
-[growling]

1:09:26.510 --> 1:09:28.555
Don't move.

1:09:33.169 --> 1:09:35.040
-[Mare gasps]
-Okay, look away from him.

1:09:35.083 --> 1:09:36.563
Don't look into his eyes.

1:09:36.607 --> 1:09:39.523
Just move away
from this window.

1:09:39.566 --> 1:09:42.482
-[snarls]
-Move into the seat.

1:09:42.526 --> 1:09:44.180
Stay calm. I'm watching him.

1:09:44.223 --> 1:09:45.964
-Norah. Shh.
-Mare, are you okay?

1:09:46.007 --> 1:09:47.444
-You have to stay still.
-MARTIN: There you go, boy.

1:09:47.487 --> 1:09:48.575
-Are you okay?
-It's okay. Shh.

1:09:48.619 --> 1:09:50.186
You have to stay still, okay?

1:09:50.229 --> 1:09:51.839
Okay, I think
we're gonna be good.

1:09:51.883 --> 1:09:54.407
[all screaming, grunting]

1:09:56.409 --> 1:09:58.411
The car's gonna tip! Go, guys!

1:09:58.455 --> 1:10:00.108
-MARE: Go, Norah! Now!
-MARTIN: Go! Get out!

1:10:00.152 --> 1:10:02.198
-Hide in the Land Rover now!
-[lion growling]

1:10:02.241 --> 1:10:03.590
Go, go, go, go, go!

1:10:03.634 --> 1:10:05.766
-He got me!
-Go! [yells]

1:10:05.810 --> 1:10:07.899
Come on, you bastard!

1:10:09.422 --> 1:10:11.163
[lion moans]

1:10:14.384 --> 1:10:16.473
[steam hissing]

1:10:20.781 --> 1:10:22.827
[pained moaning]

1:10:38.843 --> 1:10:40.932
♪

1:11:01.169 --> 1:11:03.215
[lion growling softly]

1:11:06.087 --> 1:11:07.350
[Martin whimpers]

1:11:07.393 --> 1:11:09.482
[lion growling]

1:11:12.616 --> 1:11:14.313
I'm sorry, boy.

1:11:16.228 --> 1:11:17.490
[growls]

1:11:20.188 --> 1:11:22.669
[lion moaning in pain]

1:11:25.629 --> 1:11:27.718
[insects chirping]

1:11:34.638 --> 1:11:37.118
[flame whooshes in distance]

1:11:47.781 --> 1:11:49.174
-Norah.
-Dad!

1:11:49.217 --> 1:11:50.654
NATE:
Shit. What's the fire?

1:11:50.697 --> 1:11:52.873
-The truck went off the cliff.
-Where's Mare?

1:11:52.917 --> 1:11:54.310
She's inside, but she got hurt.

1:11:54.353 --> 1:11:55.963
-She got hurt?
-Yeah, by the lion.

1:11:56.007 --> 1:11:58.270
-Hey. Mare.
-Dad.

1:11:58.314 --> 1:11:59.706
-You okay?
-I don't know.

1:11:59.750 --> 1:12:01.317
-I think I'm okay.
-All right?

1:12:01.360 --> 1:12:02.970
Where's Uncle Martin? Huh?

1:12:03.014 --> 1:12:04.842
He was in the cruiser
when it rolled over.

1:12:04.885 --> 1:12:06.365
Dad, I don't think he made it.

1:12:06.409 --> 1:12:07.801
-What?
-[pained whimpering]

1:12:07.845 --> 1:12:09.063
Let me take a look.

1:12:09.107 --> 1:12:10.891
-Oh, my God.
-Is it bad?

1:12:10.935 --> 1:12:12.980
-No, no, no, no. No, no.
It's not bad. -Okay.

1:12:13.024 --> 1:12:15.461
Uh, I just got to put some,
uh, pressure on it, okay?

1:12:15.505 --> 1:12:17.028
-Okay.
-All right?

1:12:17.071 --> 1:12:18.812
-Norah, you okay?
-Yeah.

1:12:18.856 --> 1:12:20.727
-[groans]
-Are you okay?

1:12:20.771 --> 1:12:22.642
-All right, just lean forward
a little bit like this. -Okay.

1:12:22.686 --> 1:12:24.557
-All right.
-NORAH: It's okay, Mare.

1:12:24.601 --> 1:12:26.385
Okay.

1:12:26.429 --> 1:12:27.778
All right. Look at me.

1:12:27.821 --> 1:12:29.301
-Look at me. Okay?
-Okay.

1:12:29.345 --> 1:12:30.955
-[pained whimpering]
-Okay.

1:12:30.998 --> 1:12:32.565
-We're good. You all right?
-It's okay, Mare.

1:12:32.609 --> 1:12:34.306
-Yeah.
-Okay. It's all right.

1:12:34.350 --> 1:12:37.004
-It's okay, Mare.
-It's all right.

1:12:37.048 --> 1:12:38.745
-It's okay.
-Just stay here, okay?

1:12:38.789 --> 1:12:40.051
Okay.

1:12:40.094 --> 1:12:41.792
It's okay, Mare. You're okay.

1:12:41.835 --> 1:12:44.098
[fire crackling and rumbling]

1:12:44.142 --> 1:12:46.187
♪

1:12:51.628 --> 1:12:53.281
Martin.

1:13:01.333 --> 1:13:02.943
[sniffs]

1:13:10.124 --> 1:13:12.213
♪

1:13:21.919 --> 1:13:23.790
All right, guys.

1:13:23.834 --> 1:13:26.750
We're trying to backtrack from
where we was yesterday, okay?

1:13:26.793 --> 1:13:29.448
-Okay. -I don't think
we got enough fuel, so...

1:13:29.492 --> 1:13:30.841
keep an eye out for something

1:13:30.884 --> 1:13:32.451
that we might have seen,
all right?

1:13:32.495 --> 1:13:35.019
-Okay. Okay.
-Okay?

1:13:35.062 --> 1:13:37.500
Mare, you okay?

1:13:37.543 --> 1:13:39.066
-I'm okay.
-[engine revving]

1:13:39.110 --> 1:13:40.633
I'm just a little nauseous.

1:13:40.677 --> 1:13:42.635
-All right. Look...
-[Mare groans]

1:13:42.679 --> 1:13:44.158
-All right. Okay.
-It's okay.

1:13:44.202 --> 1:13:45.682
Hey, if you feel like
you got to throw up,

1:13:45.725 --> 1:13:47.335
I need you to breathe
through it, all right?

1:13:47.379 --> 1:13:48.902
I don't want you
to strain your abdomen.

1:13:48.946 --> 1:13:50.817
-Okay. -I don't know
how deep that wound is.

1:13:50.861 --> 1:13:52.732
You understand?
Let me see you do it.

1:13:52.776 --> 1:13:54.473
-Let me see. There you go.
-[taking deep breaths]

1:13:54.517 --> 1:13:56.214
Keep your eyes
on the horizon, okay?

1:13:56.257 --> 1:13:57.520
-Okay.
-NORAH: You're gonna be okay.

1:13:57.563 --> 1:13:59.217
There you go.

1:13:59.260 --> 1:14:02.089
-No, no, no.
-[Mare whimpering]

1:14:02.133 --> 1:14:03.395
-Dad, look.
-What?

1:14:03.439 --> 1:14:04.831
The lions.

1:14:04.875 --> 1:14:06.920
That's the pride
that Banji showed us.

1:14:06.964 --> 1:14:08.966
NATE:  Yeah, there was a school
right around the corner.

1:14:09.009 --> 1:14:10.358
NORAH:
Yeah, right up here.

1:14:10.402 --> 1:14:12.448
♪

1:14:17.540 --> 1:14:19.193
MARE: Wait, Dad.
Dad, why are we stopping?

1:14:19.237 --> 1:14:21.282
I don't want to run out of gas
in the middle of nowhere.

1:14:21.326 --> 1:14:22.980
Not with you in this state.

1:14:23.023 --> 1:14:24.895
I'll see if I can find
something to dress the wound.

1:14:24.938 --> 1:14:26.374
-But, Dad, we...
-Norah, come on.

1:14:26.418 --> 1:14:27.811
-We should keep driving.
-No, no, no, I know,

1:14:27.854 --> 1:14:29.203
but there's got to be
something.

1:14:29.247 --> 1:14:30.509
A first aid kit, water.

1:14:30.553 --> 1:14:31.902
-Dad, I'll be okay.
-I know.

1:14:31.945 --> 1:14:33.730
-No, we should go.
-Honey, I know.

1:14:33.773 --> 1:14:35.732
I got to find something
to fix you up first.

1:14:35.775 --> 1:14:37.081
Do you understand?

1:14:37.124 --> 1:14:38.474
Okay, Norah,
I want you to hold this

1:14:38.517 --> 1:14:39.866
-and to stay close, all right?
-Okay.

1:14:39.910 --> 1:14:41.259
-And be careful.
-Okay.

1:14:41.302 --> 1:14:43.261
-One, two, three.
-[Mare whimpers]

1:14:43.304 --> 1:14:45.524
Okay. There you go. Go, go, go.

1:14:45.568 --> 1:14:47.178
-[whimpers] Stop.
-No, no, no, no.

1:14:47.221 --> 1:14:48.875
It's all right. It's all right.
It's all right.

1:14:48.919 --> 1:14:50.529
Okay.

1:14:52.792 --> 1:14:54.968
Keep going, honey. Keep going.

1:15:05.065 --> 1:15:07.633
[Mare whimpering]

1:15:07.677 --> 1:15:09.330
Come on.

1:15:09.374 --> 1:15:11.245
-All right?
-Yeah.

1:15:14.988 --> 1:15:16.599
Hello?

1:15:16.642 --> 1:15:18.035
Is anybody here?

1:15:18.078 --> 1:15:20.559
Dad, what is this place?

1:15:20.603 --> 1:15:22.648
Some kind of poachers' lodge.

1:15:22.692 --> 1:15:24.781
Poachers like
that we saw last night?

1:15:24.824 --> 1:15:27.740
No. Yes, but they're not
gonna come here, okay?

1:15:27.784 --> 1:15:29.394
-Okay.
-All right, put that down.

1:15:29.437 --> 1:15:31.396
Hey. All right, Mare.

1:15:31.439 --> 1:15:33.006
I want you to breathe,
all right?

1:15:33.050 --> 1:15:35.139
I'm gonna take a look at it.

1:15:35.182 --> 1:15:36.749
-Okay.
-How does it feel?

1:15:36.793 --> 1:15:38.403
-It hurts.
-Hurts? Yeah.

1:15:38.446 --> 1:15:40.100
-Bad.
-Okay.

1:15:40.144 --> 1:15:42.015
I'm gonna need to find
something to dress that, okay?

1:15:42.059 --> 1:15:43.408
Okay.

1:15:43.451 --> 1:15:45.062
Dad, it smells
really bad in here.

1:15:45.105 --> 1:15:47.238
Yeah, I know.

1:15:47.281 --> 1:15:49.719
All right. Um...

1:15:51.634 --> 1:15:54.332
-Hang on. -Mare,
we're gonna be okay, okay?

1:15:54.375 --> 1:15:57.596
-We need to find, like,
a medical box... -It's okay.

1:15:57.640 --> 1:15:59.337
NORAH: I'll be right back.
We're gonna bring something.

1:15:59.380 --> 1:16:00.947
-...or something, okay?
-MARE: Okay.

1:16:00.991 --> 1:16:02.470
-NORAH: Okay.
-NATE: Come on, Norah.

1:16:02.514 --> 1:16:04.603
Keep your eyes out.

1:16:04.647 --> 1:16:08.041
Something that looks like,
uh, gauze, all right?

1:16:08.085 --> 1:16:10.174
Go look over there.

1:16:10.217 --> 1:16:12.263
[rummaging]

1:16:13.699 --> 1:16:14.918
You see anything?

1:16:14.961 --> 1:16:17.224
-No.
-No?

1:16:17.268 --> 1:16:18.835
All right.

1:16:18.878 --> 1:16:20.619
Okay.

1:16:24.667 --> 1:16:27.583
-Oh, my goodness.
-Come on. Come on.

1:16:27.626 --> 1:16:29.802
God, I hate these poachers.

1:16:29.846 --> 1:16:31.935
♪

1:16:36.548 --> 1:16:38.202
[gasps]

1:16:40.378 --> 1:16:41.988
-You see anything?
-No.

1:16:42.032 --> 1:16:43.599
Nothing?

1:16:46.689 --> 1:16:48.604
Oh. Hey.

1:16:49.996 --> 1:16:51.607
Uh...

1:16:53.696 --> 1:16:55.349
-Hey, Norah.
-Yeah?

1:16:55.393 --> 1:16:57.351
-Uh, put these on the table.
-Okay.

1:16:57.395 --> 1:16:59.745
-Open them up.
-Uh-huh.

1:16:59.789 --> 1:17:02.226
-NORAH: Are you okay?
-MARE: Mm-hmm.

1:17:02.269 --> 1:17:04.054
NORAH: Hang on, Mare.
Just keep breathing, okay?

1:17:04.097 --> 1:17:05.533
MARE [whimpering]:
But it hurts.

1:17:05.577 --> 1:17:06.839
NORAH: I-I know
it really hurts, but...

1:17:06.883 --> 1:17:08.275
NATE:
All right, Mare. You're up.

1:17:08.319 --> 1:17:10.887
This is gonna hurt
a little bit, okay?

1:17:10.930 --> 1:17:12.802
I want you to just be brave.

1:17:12.845 --> 1:17:14.978
All right,
I'm gonna wash my hands

1:17:15.021 --> 1:17:16.806
and pour a little alcohol
on it.

1:17:16.849 --> 1:17:18.155
[Mare whimpering]

1:17:18.198 --> 1:17:20.461
All right, watch your hand now.

1:17:20.505 --> 1:17:21.985
All right.

1:17:22.028 --> 1:17:23.769
Okay, it's gonna hurt.
All right?

1:17:23.813 --> 1:17:25.510
Get that ready for me.

1:17:25.553 --> 1:17:26.946
-It's okay.
-[groaning]

1:17:26.990 --> 1:17:28.426
I know. I know.

1:17:28.469 --> 1:17:30.646
-I got to get it
right in there. -It's okay.

1:17:30.689 --> 1:17:31.951
-Okay.
-How's it look?

1:17:31.995 --> 1:17:33.779
Well, it's an animal wound,

1:17:33.823 --> 1:17:35.694
so it's prone
to infection, okay?

1:17:35.738 --> 1:17:39.219
But the laceration goes deep,

1:17:39.263 --> 1:17:42.092
but it doesn't seem
to touch any organs.

1:17:42.135 --> 1:17:43.746
All right?

1:17:43.789 --> 1:17:45.573
-Where's the other one?
-I feel... I feel sick, Dad.

1:17:45.617 --> 1:17:47.663
You feel sick? Yeah.

1:17:47.706 --> 1:17:49.839
The nausea,
that's from the dehydration

1:17:49.882 --> 1:17:51.623
and the blood loss, all right?

1:17:51.667 --> 1:17:53.233
But, hey, listen. Guess what.

1:17:53.277 --> 1:17:54.713
You're gonna be better.

1:17:54.757 --> 1:17:56.497
Bought ourselves
some time, okay?

1:17:56.541 --> 1:17:57.847
-All right?
-Okay.

1:17:57.890 --> 1:17:59.718
I think you're gonna be okay.

1:17:59.762 --> 1:18:02.199
All right? For now.

1:18:02.242 --> 1:18:04.201
-For now? What?
-[Nate chuckles]

1:18:04.244 --> 1:18:05.768
Okay, I'm playing. I'm playing.

1:18:05.811 --> 1:18:07.595
All right, girls, listen,
I'm gonna go look around

1:18:07.639 --> 1:18:09.206
and see if I can find
some water.

1:18:09.249 --> 1:18:10.686
I need you to stay here,
all right?

1:18:10.729 --> 1:18:12.557
-No, Dad. What? No.
-Hey, no, no, no.

1:18:12.600 --> 1:18:14.341
I need you to look after your
sister, okay? Can you do that?

1:18:14.385 --> 1:18:16.039
She's got me, Dad.

1:18:16.082 --> 1:18:17.605
[chuckles] All right.

1:18:17.649 --> 1:18:19.346
-I'll be right back.
-MARE: Hurry up, Dad.

1:18:19.390 --> 1:18:21.044
We're gonna be out of here.

1:18:21.087 --> 1:18:23.350
[Mare whimpering, groaning]

1:18:23.394 --> 1:18:25.918
NORAH: It's okay, Mare.
Just hold my hand.

1:18:25.962 --> 1:18:28.138
-Okay?
-MARE: This looks bad.

1:18:28.181 --> 1:18:30.270
♪

1:18:41.107 --> 1:18:43.153
[birds chirping]

1:18:50.638 --> 1:18:52.728
♪

1:19:06.742 --> 1:19:09.353
[whispers]:
Mare. Mare.

1:19:09.396 --> 1:19:11.747
-Come on, come on.
-[growling softly]

1:19:36.859 --> 1:19:39.557
[trembling breaths]

1:19:39.600 --> 1:19:41.646
[creaks loudly]

1:19:41.689 --> 1:19:43.953
[rattling]

1:19:52.875 --> 1:19:55.878
H-Hey, um, can anybody hear me?

1:19:57.618 --> 1:19:59.316
-You got to get down.
-I can't.

1:19:59.359 --> 1:20:00.839
Mare, you have to get down.

1:20:00.883 --> 1:20:02.841
-Mare. Mare, get down.
-[groaning]

1:20:02.885 --> 1:20:04.843
[snarling]

1:20:04.887 --> 1:20:06.845
NORAH:
Dad!

1:20:06.889 --> 1:20:08.934
♪

1:20:13.417 --> 1:20:16.637
-[lion growling]
-Girls, stay down! Stay down!

1:20:18.030 --> 1:20:20.337
-Stay down!
-[gun clicking]

1:20:22.426 --> 1:20:24.602
Hey, girls. You okay?

1:20:24.645 --> 1:20:26.212
All right, come on. Come on.

1:20:26.256 --> 1:20:27.605
We got to get out of here.

1:20:27.648 --> 1:20:29.825
-Wait, Dad, the gun.
-No, gun's empty.

1:20:29.868 --> 1:20:31.435
Just go that way. Go.

1:20:31.478 --> 1:20:32.784
[Mare whimpers]

1:20:32.828 --> 1:20:34.568
Okay. All right.

